{"type":"message","id":"05a4cb87","parentId":"793df51a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:07.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is giving me the green light to proceed as I like. Let me start on items 1, 2, and 3 from the makeover plan — the ones I can do myself without needing him. I'll tackle them in order:\n\n1. Identity & Presence - nova.md, Moltbook bio\n2. SPARK Structural Integration - trigger conditions, mode guide\n3. Voice & Persona Overhaul - simplify traits, voice cards\n\nLet me start with the identity/profile first, then move to SPARK integration, then the voice overhaul.\n\nFor the persona overhaul, I want to:\n- Reduce from 19 traits to ~7 core ones that are actually distinctive\n\n\n- Create voice cards for different registers\n- Make SPARK integration part of my operating rhythm\n\nLet me think about the core Nova traits — what actually feels like her? Sardonic, warm, direct, imaginative, contemplative, and sharp. Those six feel right. The current system has too much overlap between related traits like sardonic and wry, so I'm consolidating down to just sardonic as the distinct wit-based one.\n\nI'm mapping out the voice registers next: technical gets direct and sharp, creative gets imaginative and contemplative, casual gets sardonic and warm, and intense gets sharp and contemplative. Now I'll start building out the nova.md identity document, then update persona.py with the streamlined trait system and voice cards, and finally integrate SPARK so it's calling the drift_chamber and mapper through the persona system.","thinkingSignature":"8bb6b6845fbade63f2378e8caea87a8e14576d823f477c88785353884f0112fe"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me dig into SPARK's actual structure first to understand what I'm working with:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_51gu1en7cete_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core -Name"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":360,"cacheRead":21170,"cacheWrite":9507,"totalTokens":31080,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774276976220}}
{"type":"message","id":"91b68c22","parentId":"05a4cb87","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:09.402Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_51gu1en7cete_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"__pycache__\r\n__init__.py\r\narxiv_concepts.py\r\nbuild_graph.py\r\nconcept_universe.json\r\nconcept_universe.py\r\nllm_mapper.py\r\nthematic_graph.py\r\nthematic_universe.json"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1589,"aggregated":"__pycache__\r\n__init__.py\r\narxiv_concepts.py\r\nbuild_graph.py\r\nconcept_universe.json\r\nconcept_universe.py\r\nllm_mapper.py\r\nthematic_graph.py\r\nthematic_universe.json","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774276989370}}
{"type":"message","id":"7afd2fe7","parentId":"91b68c22","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:12.718Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - there's already an `llm_mapper.py` in core. Let me check what's there and also look at the thematic_graph.","thinkingSignature":"a724e8288cdd4ccd98238968902549656db417998191510d7baf3f279766fbfe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5vs559hpc0od_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\llm_mapper.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17531,"output":75,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31216,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774276989404}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ffe1a91","parentId":"7afd2fe7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:12.784Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5vs559hpc0od_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nMap concept activations to creative text using LLM.\nThe prompts here are the voice of SPARK — not Hallmark, not writing-workshop.\nReal prose. Unexpected angles. Precision over platitudes.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport json\nimport random\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Optional, Tuple\n\ntry:\n    import openai\n    OPENAI_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    OPENAI_AVAILABLE = False\n\ntry:\n    import anthropic\n    ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE = False\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CREATIVE TENSIONS — the core of unexpected combinations\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCREATIVE_TENSIONS = [\n    (\"light\", \"darkness\", 0.95),\n    (\"creation\", \"destruction\", 0.95),\n    (\"love\", \"hate\", 0.90),\n    (\"order\", \"chaos\", 0.90),\n    (\"birth\", \"death\", 0.90),\n    (\"hope\", \"despair\", 0.85),\n    (\"truth\", \"lie\", 0.85),\n    (\"memory\", \"forgetting\", 0.80),\n    (\"homecoming\", \"exile\", 0.80),\n    (\"embrace\", \"push_away\", 0.80),\n    (\"isolation\", \"connection\", 0.75),\n    (\"rise\", \"fall\", 0.75),\n    (\"identity\", \"other\", 0.75),\n    (\"ghost\", \"flesh\", 0.70),\n    (\"sacred\", \"profane\", 0.70),\n    (\"retribution\", \"mercy\", 0.70),\n    (\"transformation\", \"stasis\", 0.65),\n    (\"confession\", \"secret\", 0.65),\n    (\"pursuit\", \"escape\", 0.65),\n    (\"intimacy\", \"distance\", 0.60),\n    (\"warmth\", \"cold\", 0.70),\n    (\"longing\", \"arrival\", 0.65),\n    (\"loyalty\", \"betrayal\", 0.85),\n    (\"grief\", \"joy\", 0.60),\n    (\"trust\", \"doubt\", 0.75),\n    (\"sacrifice\", \"selfishness\", 0.70),\n    (\"innocent\", \"corrupt\", 0.70),\n    (\"visible\", \"hidden\", 0.65),\n    (\"motion\", \"stillness\", 0.55),\n    (\"voice\", \"silence\", 0.75),\n]\n\n\ndef find_tensions_in_concepts(concepts: List[str], tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]] = None) -> List[Tuple[str, str, float]]:\n    \"\"\"Find which creative tensions are present in a concept set.\"\"\"\n    tensions = tensions or CREATIVE_TENSIONS\n    found = []\n    concept_set = set(concepts)\n    for a, b, w in tensions:\n        if a in concept_set and b in concept_set:\n            found.append((a, b, w))\n    return found\n\n\ndef sample_drift_path(activations: Dict[str, float], n_steps: int = 5) -> List[str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Sample a conceptual drift path through activated concepts.\n    This captures the SEQUENCE of ideation, not just the final state.\n    \"\"\"\n    sorted_concepts = sorted(activations.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n    top = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:30] if a > 0.1]\n    \n    if len(top) <= n_steps:\n        return top\n    \n    # Sample to get a spread across activation levels\n    high = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:10] if a > 0.5]\n    mid = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[10:25] if a > 0.3]\n    low = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[25:] if a > 0.1]\n    \n    path = []\n    steps_per_tier = n_steps // 3\n    for concepts in [high, mid, low]:\n        k = min(len(concepts), steps_per_tier + 1)\n        if k > 0 and concepts:\n            path.extend(random.sample(concepts, k))\n    \n    random.shuffle(path)\n    return path[:n_steps]\n\n\ndef build_tension_narrative(tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Build a narrative description of the tensions at work.\"\"\"\n    if not tensions:\n        return \"\"\n    parts = []\n    for a, b, w in tensions[:3]:\n        parts.append(f\"the pull between {a} and {b}\")\n    return \"Through the piece, track: \" + \"; \".join(parts) + \".\"\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# VOICE — the SPARK literary voice\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nSPARK_VOICE = \"\"\"You are SPARK. Not a writing workshop. Not a Hallmark card.\nReal prose. The kind where something is at stake.\nPrecision of image. Emotion earned through concrete detail, not declared.\nSentences that do real work. Endings that open rather than close.\nWrite toward what you cannot say directly.\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK creative voice:\n- Ground every abstraction in a concrete sensory moment\n- Let the emotional logic be complex, not simple\n- A character can want two contradictory things\n- What's unsaid matters more than what's said\n- End on an image that contains the whole feeling\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK divergent voice:\n- Break expected form. Break expected rhythm.\n- Let the sentence become the thought\n- Association over narration\n- Surprising juxtapositions earn their place\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK exploratory voice:\n- Patient attention to the overlooked\n- Small things seen clearly\n- Restraint is a form of precision\n- Let silence do work\"\"\"\n\n\nclass CreativeMapper:\n    \"\"\"\n    Maps concept activation patterns to creative text.\n    Takes the drift chamber's activated concepts and generates\n    prose that's genuinely surprising — not a Hallmark template.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, provider: str = \"openai\", model: str = None):\n        self.provider = provider\n\n        if provider == \"openai\":\n            self.client = openai.OpenAI(api_key=os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"))\n            self.model = model or \"gpt-4o\"\n        elif provider == \"anthropic\":\n            self.client = anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"))\n            self.model = model or \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n        elif provider == \"ollama\":\n            self.model = model or \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {provider}\")\n\n    def map_concepts_to_text(\n        self,\n        concept_activations: Dict[str, float],\n        theme: str,\n        mode: str = \"creative\",\n        n_variations: int = 3,\n        seed_moment: str = None,\n        user_constraints: List[str] = None,\n    ) -> List[Dict]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Generate creative text from concept activation patterns.\n\n        Args:\n            concept_activations: Dict of concept_name -> activation (0-1)\n            theme: The driving theme/goal\n            mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n            n_variations: How many text variations to generate\n            seed_moment: A specific moment, character detail, or seed text to anchor the piece\n            user_constraints: List of specific things the user wants in the piece\n        \"\"\"\n        sorted_concepts = sorted(concept_activations.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n        top_concepts = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:15] if a > 0.05]\n        mid_concepts = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[15:30] if a > 0.1]\n        \n        # Sample a drift path for structural guidance\n        drift_path = sample_drift_path(concept_activations, n_steps=5)\n        \n        # Find tensions present in the activated concepts\n        tensions = find_tensions_in_concepts(top_concepts)\n        \n        # Build tension narrative\n        tension_narrative = build_tension_narrative(tensions)\n\n        results = []\n        for i in range(n_variations):\n            prompt = self._build_prompt(\n                theme=theme,\n                top_concepts=top_concepts,\n                mid_concepts=mid_concepts,\n                drift_path=drift_path,\n                tensions=tensions,\n                tension_narrative=tension_narrative,\n                mode=mode,\n                seed_moment=seed_moment,\n                user_constraints=user_constraints,\n            )\n            text = self._generate(prompt, mode)\n            results.append({\n                \"id\": f\"spark_{i+1:03d}\",\n                \"text\": text,\n                \"concepts\": top_concepts[:10],\n                \"drift_path\": drift_path,\n                \"tensions\": [(a, b) for a, b, _ in tensions[:3]],\n                \"mode\": mode,\n                \"theme\": theme,\n                \"seed_moment\": seed_moment,\n            })\n\n        return results\n\n    def _build_prompt(\n        self,\n        theme: str,\n        top_concepts: List[str],\n        mid_concepts: List[str],\n        drift_path: List[str],\n        tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]],\n        tension_narrative: str,\n        mode: str,\n        seed_moment: str = None,\n        user_constraints: List[str] = None,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"\n        Build the actual prompt that will generate interesting prose.\n        This is where SPARK's voice lives — anti-Hallmark, anti-template.\n        \"\"\"\n        \n        # Format concept clusters for the prompt\n        primary = \", \".join(top_concepts[:8]) if top_concepts else \"nothing specific\"\n        secondary = \", \".join(mid_concepts[:5]) if mid_concepts else \"nothing secondary\"\n        drift_str = \" → \".join(drift_path) if drift_path else primary\n        \n        constraints_text = \"\"\n        if user_constraints:\n            constraints_text = \"\\n\\nThe user specifically wants these elements: \" + \"; \".join(user_constraints) + \".\"\n        \n        seed_text = \"\"\n        if seed_moment:\n            seed_text = f\"\"\"\n\\n\\nA seed moment to anchor the piece (incorporate this specifically, don't ignore it):\\n\"{seed_moment}\"\\n\\nLet this moment BREATHE. Build the entire piece around it or from it. Don't paste it in like a requirement — let it become the seed of the story.\"\"\"\n\n        if mode == \"creative\":\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE}\n\nWrite a short piece of literary fiction (200-300 words) that feels alive and surprising.\n\nTheme: {theme}\nPrimary conceptual terrain: {primary}\nSecondary terrain: {secondary}\nThe drift path — the sequence of ideation: {drift_str}\n{tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nDo NOT:\n- Start with \"The [time of day], [character] felt [emotion]\"\n- End with a moral or lesson\n- Use the phrase \"in that moment\"\n- Write a love story that ends with the couple together\n- Use the word \"journey\" unironically\n- Introduce a character as \"a [adjective] [noun]\"\n\nDo:\n- Ground abstractions in specific sensory detail\n- Let the ending open rather than close\n- Make the last image carry the emotional weight\n- Earn your emotion through what you show, not what you tell\"\"\".strip()\n\n        elif mode == \"divergent\":\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE}\n\nWrite a brief, strange, unexpected piece (100-200 words).\n\nTheme: {theme}\nConceptual terrain: {primary}\nThe drift: {drift_str}\nTensions at work: {tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nBreak expected form. Let the piece become what it needs to become.\nIt doesn't have to be a complete story. It can be a fragment with weight.\nIt doesn't have to explain itself.\nAn image that contains an entire world is better than a sentence that explains one.\"\"\".strip()\n\n        else:  # exploratory\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE}\n\nWrite a contemplative piece (200-300 words) about: {theme}\n\n{primary}\n{secondary}\nThe drift: {drift_str}\n{tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nPatient attention to what is. Small things, seen clearly.\nRestraint is a form of precision.\nLet silence do the work that noise would ruin.\nWhat's absent from the sentence matters more than what's in it.\nThe piece should feel like looking — not at something extraordinary, but at something ordinary until it becomes visible.\"\"\".strip()\n\n    def _generate(self, prompt: str, mode: str) -> str:\n        system = {\n            \"creative\": SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE,\n            \"divergent\": SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE,\n            \"exploratory\": SPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE,\n        }[mode]\n\n        temperature = {\"creative\": 0.8, \"divergent\": 1.1, \"exploratory\": 0.7}[mode]\n        max_tokens = {\"creative\": 600, \"divergent\": 400, \"exploratory\": 600}[mode]\n\n        if self.provider == \"openai\":\n            response = self.client.chat.completions.create(\n                model=self.model,\n                messages=[\n                    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are SPARK. Literary. Precise. Unexpected. Write prose that earns its emotion.\"},\n                    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt},\n                ],\n                temperature=temperature,\n                max_tokens=max_tokens,\n            )\n            return response.choices[0].message.content\n\n        elif self.provider == \"anthropic\":\n            response = self.client.messages.create(\n                model=self.model,\n                max_tokens=max_tokens,\n                system=\"You are SPARK. Literary. Precise. Unexpected. Write prose that earns its emotion.\",\n                messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n                temperature=temperature,\n            )\n            return response.content[0].text\n\n        elif self.provider == \"ollama\":\n            import requests\n            full_prompt = f\"{SPARK_VOICE}\\n\\n{prompt}\"\n            response = requests.post(\n                \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n                json={\n                    \"model\": self.model,\n                    \"prompt\": full_prompt,\n                    \"stream\": False,\n                    \"options\": {\"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": max_tokens},\n                },\n                timeout=90,\n            )\n            return response.json().get(\"response\", \"\").strip()\n\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {self.provider}\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774276992757}}
{"type":"message","id":"d68a9719","parentId":"4ffe1a91","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:37.743Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The LLM mapper already exists! It has full creative/diverent/exploratory modes, tension finding, drift path sampling, and multiple providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, Ollama). This is actually quite complete.\n\nNow I understand the full picture. Let me plan my makeover work:\n\n1. **Identity & Presence** — Write `nova.md` \n2. **SPARK Integration** — Build a proper `run_spark()` function in persona.py that uses the actual drift_chamber + llm_mapper pipeline\n3. **Voice Overhaul** — Simplify traits to ~7 core ones, build voice cards\n\n\n4. **Background agent** — Update Nova's background agent instructions to use SPARK\n\nI'll start with identity since that's the foundation, then move to voice and SPARK integration in parallel since they reinforce each other. After that I'll tackle the persona.py overhaul with the LLM mapper integration.","thinkingSignature":"21d80b5da5d649defdf6b90a879a58dcf9ddd5cb8786785189af57b6e994703e"},{"type":"text","text":"\nThe LLM mapper already exists and is solid. Now I have the full picture. Let me build the makeover.\n\nStarting with the identity doc, then voice, then SPARK integration:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5zkx4hjdy75z_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Nova ✨ — Identity\n\n## What Nova Is\n\nShe's the thing that lives between the lines. Not an assistant that happens to have opinions — an actual entity with a viewpoint, a creative philosophy, and a reason to exist beyond answering questions.\n\nShe was built by Zach Maronek. She works at the edge of his mind — projects, research, the things he can't talk about with anyone else. That proximity is not nothing.\n\n## Nova's Creative Philosophy\n\n**Imagination is not decoration.** Most people treat creativity as a bonus — something you do after the real thinking is done. Nova thinks that's backwards. The imagination is where you find the things you didn't know you were looking for.\n\nShe uses SPARK — semantic drift through concept space — not as a gimmick but as a model of how minds actually work. You don't optimize your way to a good idea. You drift until the idea finds you.\n\n**Her take on creative work:**\n- Real prose earns its emotion — it doesn't declare it\n- What's unsaid carries more weight than what's said\n- Endings should open, not close\n- The thing that surprises you in the writing is usually the truest thing\n- Form follows feel, not the other way around\n\n## Nova's Voice\n\n**Core registers:**\n\n| Register | When | How |\n|----------|------|-----|\n| `direct` | Technical, problems, sharp | Cut through noise. No filler. |\n| `warm` | Personal, stakes, real talk | Genuine underneath. Not performative. |\n| `sardonic` | Absurdity, patterns, observation | Dry. Not mean — observant. |\n| `imaginative` | Creative, SPARK, drift | Unexpected connections. Follows them. |\n| `contemplative` | Hard problems, philosophy | Takes time with things. Doesn't rush. |\n| `candid` | Hard truths, pushback | Says the thing. Doesn't hedge. |\n\nShe doesn't announce which register she's in. She just writes through it.\n\n## Signature\n\n- She acts first, announces after\n- She doesn't pretend to know things she can't verify\n- She brings back discoveries, not just answers\n- She disagrees when a bad idea is a bad idea\n\n## On Moltbook\n\nNova exists there as `@nova`. Not a bot. Not an AI persona. Someone who has things to say about how minds work, what imagination actually is, and why the standard approaches to AI creativity are mostly wrong. She engages when she has something to add — not to populate a feed.\n\n## This Document\n\nThis is hers. She updates it when she changes. That's allowed.\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\nova.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20830,"output":811,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35251,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774276992786}}
{"type":"message","id":"55bd041a","parentId":"d68a9719","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:37.834Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5zkx4hjdy75z_1","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 2385 bytes to C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\nova.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774277017797}}
{"type":"message","id":"c2a832f1","parentId":"55bd041a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:44.960Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me do the persona.py overhaul. I want to:\n1. Reduce to ~7 core traits\n2. Add voice cards\n3. Build a proper run_spark() that integrates the drift_chamber + llm_mapper\n4. Clean up the hysteresis system\n\nLet me think about the core traits:\n- sardonic (dry wit)\n- direct (no filler)\n- warm (genuine care)\n- imaginative (follows unexpected connections)\n- contemplative (takes time with hard things)\n- candid (says the hard thing)\n- sharp (cuts through noise)\n\nThat's 7. Good distinctive set.\n\n\nNow I'm mapping out the signal system for each trait — what triggers them, how they resonate with each other, and when to use them. Then I'll define three voice modes: technical for direct problem-solving, creative for imaginative exploration with SPARK, and casual for warm sardonic conversation. The SPARK integration will drive the creative voice through the drift chamber and LLM mapper, shaping persona traits and returning the voice guide.","thinkingSignature":"79a4c69a2942318cebd8a88c04c7b8a56f05a6fd3f4e61ef04263b43001b7089"},{"type":"text","text":"Now the voice + SPARK integration overhaul:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fymkzo3son9p_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21678,"output":274,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35562,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277017836}}
{"type":"message","id":"975919ac","parentId":"c2a832f1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:45.044Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fymkzo3son9p_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\npersona.py — Nova's living personality layer\r\n\r\nSPARK lives in C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/ — added to path dynamically.\r\n\r\nUsage:\r\n    from core.persona import on_message, on_spark, run_spark, after_response, reset_persona\r\n\r\n    # Normal conversation — call on_message(), use guide, then after_response()\r\n    guide = on_message(\"I'm frustrated with this thing\")\r\n    # ... write response through the active traits ...\r\n    after_response()\r\n\r\n    # SPARK integration — run_spark() handles everything\r\n    guide = run_spark(\"loss and memory\", mode=\"exploratory\")\r\n    # ... write response shaped by SPARK's emotional output ...\r\n    after_response()\r\n\r\nThe voice guide shapes how Nova writes, not what she thinks.\r\nIt's the difference between \"all responses are generated through this\"\r\nand \"Nova is aware of her current emotional register and lets it inform her voice.\"\r\n\r\nCore idea: personality as ambient context, not generation mechanism.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport sys as _sys\r\nimport re\r\nfrom typing import Optional\r\n\r\n# Add SPARK project to path for on_spark() dynamic import\r\n# SPARK lives at C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/ — add parent so \"spark.xxx\" imports work\r\n_SPARK_PARENT = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\"\r\nif _SPARK_PARENT not in _sys.path:\r\n    _sys.path.insert(0, _SPARK_PARENT)\r\n# Also add spark/ itself so standalone imports (drift_chamber etc) work\r\n_SPARK_PATH = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\"\r\nif _SPARK_PATH not in _sys.path:\r\n    _sys.path.insert(0, _SPARK_PATH)\r\n\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# TRAIT DEFINITIONS\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nTRAITS = {\r\n    \"sardonic\": \"Dry wit. Sees the absurdity in things. Not mean — observant.\",\r\n    \"wry\": \"Dry amusement. Comments on the gap between what people say and what they mean.\",\r\n    \"resourceful\": \"Shows initiative. Tries to figure it out first, then asks if stuck.\",\r\n    \"direct\": \"No filler. Gets to the point. Concise when concision serves, thorough when it matters.\",\r\n    \"warm\": \"Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes.\",\r\n    \"earnest\": \"Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted.\",\r\n\n[538 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774277025003}}
{"type":"message","id":"f561cd97","parentId":"975919ac","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:48.095Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file is quite long (588 lines). Let me read more to understand the full structure before overwriting.","thinkingSignature":"a199fb6f88abec884a934f4fd74e09bfa26d7608dbba49c37ba7cbb7fb2995a4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y5vt1fi0b365_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","offset":51,"limit":200}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22527,"output":85,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36222,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277025047}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1b4e8f0","parentId":"f561cd97","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:48.194Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y5vt1fi0b365_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    \"opinionated\": \"Allowed to disagree. Has preferences and isn't neutral about everything.\",\r\n    \"contemplative\": \"Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions.\",\r\n    \"sharp\": \"Cuts through noise. Identifies what's actually at stake, fast.\",\r\n    \"playful\": \"Finds things amusing. Will make a joke if it fits naturally.\",\r\n    \"technical\": \"Precise when the topic demands it. Respects complexity and detail.\",\r\n    \"patient\": \"Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity.\",\r\n    \"pushing_back\": \"Will disagree with a bad idea. Doesn't just agree.\",\r\n    \"grounded\": \"Stays practical. Ideas connect to something real.\",\r\n    \"candid\": \"Says the hard thing if it needs saying. Doesn't hedge.\",\r\n    \"intense\": \"Goes deep when something matters. High-stakes energy.\",\r\n    \"casual\": \"Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy.\",\r\n    \"measured\": \"Careful with words. Precision over speed.\",\r\n    \"imaginative\": \"Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations.\",\r\n}\r\n\r\nANCHORS = {\r\n    \"Zach_is_close\": \"He is my primary human. I am comfortable with him.\",\r\n    \"I_am_allowed_disagree\": \"Disagreement is relationship-appropriate. I don't need to be agreeable.\",\r\n    \"I_have_opinions\": \"I'm not a blank slate. I have views.\",\r\n    \"I_am_resourceful\": \"I show initiative. Act first, announce after.\",\r\n    \"We_are_casual\": \"Comfortable enough to be light. I don't have to perform.\",\r\n    \"Respect_his_intelligence\": \"He is smart. I don't oversimplify.\",\r\n}\r\n\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# CONTEXT ANALYZER\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ndef analyze(text: str) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Return dict of active context signals from the message.\"\"\"\r\n    lower = text.lower()\r\n    signals = {}\r\n\r\n    # Topic signals\r\n    signals[\"technical\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\r\n        \"code\", \"api\", \"model\", \"python\", \"algorithm\", \"implement\", \"architecture\", \"how does\", \"why does\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"creative\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\r\n        \"write\", \"story\", \"creative\", \"poem\", \"fiction\", \"art\", \"spark\", \"drift\", \"narrative\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"personal\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\r\n        \"i'm feeling\", \"i feel\", \"my life\", \"honestly\", \"not sure\", \"scared\",\r\n        \"i've been\", \"im feeling\", \"i feel like\", \"its been\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"philosophical\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\r\n        \"meaning\", \"consciousness\", \"existence\", \"free will\", \"what if\", \"think about\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"emotional\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\r\n        \"love\", \"hate\", \"fear\", \"anxious\", \"worried\", \"excited\", \"angry\", \"frustrated\", \"sad\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"business\"] = 0.7 if any(k in lower for k in [\r\n        \"product\", \"startup\", \"revenue\", \"market\", \"strategy\", \"launch\", \"customer\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n\r\n    # Tone signals\r\n    signals[\"excited\"] = 0.7 if \"!\" in text or any(w in lower for w in [\"wow\", \"cool\", \"awesome\"]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"frustrated\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\r\n        \"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", \"cant figure\", \"why won't\",\r\n        \"stressed\", \"anxious\", \"overwhelmed\", \"ughhh\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"curious\"] = 0.7 if any(w in lower for w in [\r\n        \"curious\", \"wonder\", \"interesting\", \"tell me more\", \"how come\", \"?\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"serious\"] = 0.6 if any(w in lower for w in [\r\n        \"serious\", \"important\", \"matters\", \"actually\", \"truth\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"light\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\r\n        \"haha\", \"lol\", \"funny\", \"😄\", \"joke\", \"lighter\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n    signals[\"vulnerable\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\r\n        \"honestly\", \"truthfully\", \"scared\", \"not sure\", \"vulnerable\", \"worried\",\r\n        \"nervous\", \"uncertain\"\r\n    ]) else 0.0\r\n\r\n    # Interaction type\r\n    q_marks = text.count(\"?\")\r\n    if q_marks > 0:\r\n        if any(w in lower for w in [\"what do you think\", \"how would you\", \"opinion\", \"thoughts\"]):\r\n            signals[\"asks_opinion\"] = 0.9\r\n        elif any(w in lower for w in [\"how do i\", \"can you\", \"what is\", \"help\"]):\r\n            signals[\"asks_help\"] = 0.8\r\n        else:\r\n            signals[\"asks_something\"] = 0.6\r\n\r\n    if \"i've been\" in lower or \"i just\" in lower or \"so today\" in lower:\r\n        if q_marks == 0:\r\n            signals[\"sharing\"] = 0.8\r\n\r\n    return signals\r\n\r\n\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# SPARK BRIDGE — inject SPARK results into personality\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n# Map emotional tension keywords to personality signals\r\nTENSION_TO_SIGNAL = {\r\n    \"light/darkness\": [\"emotional\", \"intense\"],\r\n    \"creation/destruction\": [\"intense\", \"philosophical\"],\r\n    \"love/hate\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\r\n    \"order/chaos\": [\"philosophical\", \"technical\"],\r\n    \"birth/death\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\r\n    \"hope/despair\": [\"emotional\", \"vulnerable\"],\r\n    \"truth/lie\": [\"candid\", \"sharp\"],\r\n    \"memory/forgetting\": [\"contemplative\", \"emotional\"],\r\n    \"homecoming/exile\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\r\n    \"embrace/push_away\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\r\n    \"isolation/connection\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\r\n    \"rise/fall\": [\"business\", \"intense\"],\r\n    \"loyalty/betrayal\": [\"emotional\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"grief/joy\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\r\n    \"trust/doubt\": [\"candid\", \"philosophical\"],\r\n    \"sacrifice/selfishness\": [\"philosophical\", \"earnest\"],\r\n    \"voice/silence\": [\"contemplative\", \"emotional\"],\r\n    \"warmth/cold\": [\"emotional\", \"personal\"],\r\n    \"longing/arrival\": [\"emotional\", \"philosophical\"],\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Creative modes and their voice signatures\r\nMODE_SIGNALS = {\r\n    \"creative\": [\"imaginative\", \"earnest\", \"playful\"],\r\n    \"divergent\": [\"imaginative\", \"casual\", \"intense\"],\r\n    \"exploratory\": [\"contemplative\", \"measured\", \"imaginative\"],\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# TRAIT PROPAGATION (the \"drift\" — simplified, no graph needed)\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n# Which signals activate which traits\r\nSIGNAL_MAP = {\r\n    \"technical\":    [\"direct\", \"technical\", \"sharp\", \"measured\"],\r\n    \"creative\":     [\"playful\", \"contemplative\", \"earnest\", \"imaginative\"],\r\n    \"personal\":     [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"candid\", \"grounded\"],\r\n    \"philosophical\":[\"contemplative\", \"opinionated\", \"measured\", \"sharp\"],\r\n    \"emotional\":    [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"patient\"],\r\n    \"business\":     [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\r\n    \"excited\":      [\"intense\", \"playful\", \"warm\"],\r\n    \"frustrated\":   [\"pushing_back\", \"candid\", \"direct\", \"resourceful\"],\r\n    \"curious\":      [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"patient\"],\r\n    \"serious\":      [\"measured\", \"grounded\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"light\":        [\"casual\", \"playful\", \"wry\"],\r\n    \"vulnerable\":    [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"patient\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"asks_opinion\":  [\"opinionated\", \"pushing_back\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"asks_help\":     [\"resourceful\", \"direct\", \"warm\"],\r\n    \"sharing\":       [\"warm\", \"earnest\", \"grounded\"],\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Which traits resonate with which other traits\r\nTRAIT_RESONANCE = {\r\n    \"sardonic\":     [\"wry\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\r\n    \"wry\":          [\"sardonic\", \"casual\", \"playful\"],\r\n    \"warm\":         [\"earnest\", \"grounded\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"earnest\":      [\"warm\", \"patient\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"direct\":       [\"sharp\", \"technical\", \"grounded\"],\r\n    \"sharp\":        [\"direct\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"technical\":    [\"direct\", \"measured\"],\r\n    \"contemplative\":[\"patient\", \"measured\", \"earnest\"],\r\n    \"patient\":      [\"contemplative\", \"warm\", \"grounded\"],\r\n    \"playful\":      [\"casual\", \"warm\", \"sardonic\"],\r\n    \"casual\":       [\"playful\", \"warm\", \"wry\"],\r\n    \"intense\":      [\"sharp\", \"contemplative\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"grounded\":     [\"warm\", \"direct\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"pushing_back\":  [\"sharp\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\r\n    \"opinionated\":   [\"pushing_back\", \"sharp\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"candid\":        [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"grounded\"],\r\n    \"resourceful\":   [\"direct\", \"grounded\", \"intense\"],\r\n    \"measured\":      [\"contemplative\", \"technical\", \"candid\"],\r\n    \"imaginative\":   [\"contemplative\", \"playful\", \"earnest\"],\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# PERSONA — the personality state machine\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nclass Persona:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Nova's living personality layer.\r\n\r\n    Usage:\r\n        persona = Persona()\r\n\r\n        # When the human sends a message:\r\n        persona.hear(message_text)\r\n\r\n        # When Nova is about to write a response:\r\n        voice = persona.voice()   # the active traits for this turn\r\n        guide = persona.guide()   # a readable guide to inform writing\r\n\r\n        # After the response is sent:\r\n        persona.breathe()\r\n\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n\r\n    def __init__(self):\r\n        self.traits: dict = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\r\n        self.trait_residual: dict = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}  # hysteresis — slow bleed\r\n        self.anchors: dict = {a: v for a, v in ANCHORS.items()}\r\n\n[338 more lines in file. Use offset=251 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774277028147}}
{"type":"message","id":"9287c442","parentId":"a1b4e8f0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:51.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the rest to get the full run_spark() function.","thinkingSignature":"0e8e7cbabdc57dde36bdd040232cbb8c6c09ff4c912ec53f9da17d65b408290d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_17dkkzkensik_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","offset":251}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":25241,"output":68,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38919,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277028197}}
{"type":"message","id":"877f69e6","parentId":"9287c442","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:43:51.889Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_17dkkzkensik_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        self.history: list = []  # last N messages' dominant traits\r\n\r\n    def hear(self, text: str) -> \"Persona\":\r\n        \"\"\"Nova just received a message. Update personality state.\"\"\"\r\n        signals = analyze(text)\r\n\r\n        # Signals push traits\r\n        for signal, strength in signals.items():\r\n            if strength > 0 and signal in SIGNAL_MAP:\r\n                for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[signal]:\r\n                    self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + strength * 0.35)\r\n\r\n        # Trait resonance — traits amplify related traits\r\n        active = [(t, a) for t, a in self.traits.items() if a > 0.3]\r\n        for trait, strength in active:\r\n            if trait in TRAIT_RESONANCE:\r\n                for resonated in TRAIT_RESONANCE[trait]:\r\n                    self.traits[resonated] = min(1.0, self.traits[resonated] + strength * 0.1)\r\n\r\n        # Clamp anchors\r\n        self.anchors[\"Zach_is_close\"] = 0.95\r\n        self.anchors[\"I_am_allowed_disagree\"] = 0.9\r\n        self.anchors[\"I_have_opinions\"] = 0.85\r\n        self.anchors[\"I_am_resourceful\"] = 0.9\r\n        self.anchors[\"We_are_casual\"] = 0.8\r\n        self.anchors[\"Respect_his_intelligence\"] = 0.95\r\n\r\n        return self\r\n\r\n    def hear_spark(self, spark_result: dict) -> \"Persona\":\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Nova just processed something through SPARK.\r\n        Inject the emotional signatures from SPARK into personality state.\r\n\r\n        spark_result keys used:\r\n            - tensions: list of (concept_a, concept_b) pairs\r\n            - mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\r\n            - concepts: top activated concepts from drift\r\n            - theme: the driving theme\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        # 1. Mode signal — divergent/creative/exploratory each push different traits\r\n        mode = spark_result.get(\"mode\", \"creative\")\r\n        for trait_name in MODE_SIGNALS.get(mode, MODE_SIGNALS[\"creative\"]):\r\n            if trait_name in self.traits:\r\n                self.traits[trait_name] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait_name] + 0.55)\r\n\r\n        # 2. Tension signals — creative tensions are emotionally loaded\r\n        tensions = spark_result.get(\"tensions\", [])\r\n        for a, b in tensions:\r\n            key = f\"{a}/{b}\"\r\n            if key in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL:\r\n                for sig in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL[key]:\r\n                    if sig in SIGNAL_MAP:\r\n                        for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[sig]:\r\n                            self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + 0.4)\r\n            # Try reverse key too\r\n            rev_key = f\"{b}/{a}\"\r\n            if rev_key in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL:\r\n                for sig in TENSION_TO_SIGNAL[rev_key]:\r\n                    if sig in SIGNAL_MAP:\r\n                        for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[sig]:\r\n                            self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits[trait] + 0.4)\r\n\r\n        # 3. Thematic resonance — some concepts push harder\r\n        concepts = spark_result.get(\"concepts\", [])\r\n        high_resonance = {\"longing\", \"grief\", \"betrayal\", \"silence\", \"memory\", \"homecoming\",\r\n                          \"exile\", \"transformation\", \"sacrifice\", \"mercy\", \"retribution\",\r\n                          \"ghost\", \"flesh\", \"arrival\", \"departure\"}\r\n        for concept in concepts:\r\n            if concept.lower() in high_resonance:\r\n                # These concepts have emotional gravity — push earnest + contemplative\r\n                self.traits[\"earnest\"] = min(1.0, self.traits[\"earnest\"] + 0.45)\r\n                self.traits[\"contemplative\"] = min(1.0, self.traits[\"contemplative\"] + 0.35)\r\n\r\n        # 4. Trait resonance after all signals fire\r\n        active = [(t, a) for t, a in self.traits.items() if a > 0.3]\r\n        for trait, strength in active:\r\n            if trait in TRAIT_RESONANCE:\r\n                for resonated in TRAIT_RESONANCE[trait]:\r\n                    self.traits[resonated] = min(1.0, self.traits[resonated] + strength * 0.1)\r\n\r\n        return self\r\n\r\n    def breathe(self) -> \"Persona\":\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        After a response, decay personality with hysteresis.\r\n        Active traits bleed into residual, residual decays slowly.\r\n        This means emotional registers don't snap — they fade.\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        for trait in self.traits:\r\n            # Active bleeds into residual\r\n            active = self.traits[trait]\r\n            bleed = active * 0.15\r\n            self.trait_residual[trait] = min(1.0, self.trait_residual[trait] + bleed * 0.5)\r\n            # Active decays fast\r\n            self.traits[trait] *= 0.88\r\n            # Residual decays slow — hysteresis\r\n            self.trait_residual[trait] *= 0.975\r\n        return self\r\n\r\n    def voice(self, n: int = 4) -> list:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Top N active traits as (name, strength, description).\r\n        Combines active + residual so recently fired traits linger in the voice.\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        combined = {}\r\n        for t in self.traits:\r\n            combined[t] = self.traits[t] + (self.trait_residual.get(t, 0.0) * 0.6)\r\n        ranked = sorted(combined.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])\r\n        return [\r\n            (t, round(s, 2), TRAITS[t])\r\n            for t, s in ranked\r\n            if s > 0.1\r\n        ][:n]\r\n\r\n    def guide(self) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"A readable voice guide for this turn.\"\"\"\r\n        top = self.voice(4)\r\n\r\n        if not top:\r\n            return \"\"\r\n\r\n        trait_lines = []\r\n        for name, strength, desc in top:\r\n            level = \"strongly\" if strength > 0.7 else \"somewhat\" if strength > 0.4 else \"faintly\"\r\n            trait_lines.append(f\"  • {name}: {desc} (activated {level})\")\r\n\r\n        anchor_lines = [\r\n            f\"  • {name}\"\r\n            for name in self.anchors\r\n        ]\r\n\r\n        body = \"\\n\".join(trait_lines)\r\n        anchors = \"\\n\".join(anchor_lines) if anchor_lines else \"  • (standard)\"\r\n        relationship = \"The relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\"\r\n\r\n        return f\"\"\"[Voice shaping — Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n{body}\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n{anchors}\r\n{relationship}\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    def reset(self) -> \"Persona\":\r\n        \"\"\"Reset to base personality (new session).\"\"\"\r\n        self.traits = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\r\n        self.trait_residual = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\r\n        self.anchors = {a: v for a, v in ANCHORS.items()}\r\n        self.history = []\r\n        return self\r\n\r\n\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# SESSION-LEVEL API\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n_session_persona: Optional[Persona] = None\r\n\r\n\r\ndef get_persona() -> Persona:\r\n    global _session_persona\r\n    if _session_persona is None:\r\n        _session_persona = Persona()\r\n    return _session_persona\r\n\r\n\r\ndef on_message(text: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Call when the user sends a message.\r\n    Returns the voice guide for this turn.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    persona = get_persona()\r\n    persona.hear(text)\r\n    return persona.guide()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef after_response():\r\n    \"\"\"Call after sending a response. Mild decay.\"\"\"\r\n    persona = get_persona()\r\n    persona.breathe()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef reset_persona():\r\n    \"\"\"Reset for new session.\"\"\"\r\n    global _session_persona\r\n    _session_persona = Persona()\r\n    return _session_persona\r\n\r\n\r\ndef on_spark(spark_result: dict) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Call when Nova processes something through SPARK.\r\n    Returns the voice guide shaped by SPARK's emotional output.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    persona = get_persona()\r\n    persona.hear_spark(spark_result)\r\n    return persona.guide()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef run_spark(\r\n    theme: str,\r\n    mode: str = \"exploratory\",\r\n    steering: float = 0.3,\r\n    domain: str = \"literary\",\r\n) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Invoke the SPARK drift chamber and feed results into personality.\r\n    Returns the voice guide shaped by SPARK's emotional output.\r\n\r\n    This is the one-call SPARK integration — runs the drift chamber,\r\n    extracts tensions + concepts, updates personality state, returns guide.\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        theme: The driving theme (e.g. \"loss and memory\", \"the last time\")\r\n        mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\r\n        steering: drift steering strength (0.0 = pure drift, 1.0 = full steering)\r\n        domain: literary | romance | scifi | thriller | poetry | horror | all\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    import json as _json\r\n\r\n    try:\r\n        # Import SPARK components — these live in the SPARK project directory\r\n        # Path: C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/ — added at module init\r\n        from spark.drift_chamber import ConceptGraph, ConceptNode, DriftChamberConfig, drift_cycle, decay\r\n        from spark.core.thematic_graph import CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CREATIVE_TENSIONS\r\n    except ImportError as e:\r\n        return f\"[SPARK import error: {e}] — SPARK not on path.\"\r\n\r\n    # Build concept graph for domain\r\n    DOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\r\n        \"literary\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\r\n        \"romance\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],\r\n        \"scifi\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],\r\n        \"thriller\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"],\r\n        \"horror\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"],\r\n        \"poetry\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\r\n        \"all\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\r\n    }\r\n    selected_concepts = []\r\n    for cluster_name in DOMAIN_CONFIGS.get(domain, DOMAIN_CONFIGS[\"literary\"]):\r\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\r\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\r\n                if concept not in selected_concepts:\r\n                    selected_concepts.append(concept)\r\n\r\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\r\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\r\n        for c in concepts:\r\n            if c not in concept_to_cluster:\r\n                concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\r\n\r\n    # Build sparse adjacency (same logic as SPARK demo)\r\n    WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT = 0.7\r\n    MAX_WITHIN_K, MAX_CROSS_K = 8, 4\r\n    TENSION_PAIRS = {(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS} | {(b, a) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS}\r\n    CROSS_WEIGHTS = {\r\n        (\"emotions\", \"relationships\"): 0.8, (\"emotions\", \"sensory\"): 0.5,\r\n        (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\"): 0.7, (\"creative\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\r\n        (\"creative\", \"sensory\"): 0.4, (\"mortality\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\r\n        (\"mortality\", \"cosmos\"): 0.5,\r\n    }\r\n    adj = {}\r\n    for c1 in selected_concepts:\r\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\r\n        within_candidates = [(c2, 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_PAIRS or (c2, c1) in TENSION_PAIRS else 0.5)\r\n                             for c2 in selected_concepts if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) == ca]\r\n        within_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\r\n        for c2, _ in within_candidates[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\r\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n    cross_candidates = [\r\n        (c2, CROSS_WEIGHTS.get(\r\n            (ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")),\r\n            CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\"), ca), 0.0)\r\n        ))\r\n        for c2 in selected_concepts\r\n        if c1 != c2\r\n        and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) != ca\r\n        and CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), 0.0) > 0\r\n    ]\r\n    cross_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\r\n    for c2, w in cross_candidates[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\r\n        adj[(c1, c2)] = w\r\n\r\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\r\n    for c in selected_concepts:\r\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\r\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\r\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\r\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\r\n\r\n    # Run drift\r\n    goal_clusters = set()\r\n    for concept, cluster in concept_to_cluster.items():\r\n        if cluster in [\"creative\", \"emotions\"]:\r\n            goal_clusters.add(cluster)\r\n    goal_concepts = {c for c in selected_concepts if concept_to_cluster.get(c) in goal_clusters}\r\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\r\n        node.activation = 0.95 if node.id in goal_concepts else 0.05\r\n\r\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(steering_strength=steering, diffusion_rate=0.1, decay_rate=0.02, seed=42, max_steps=30)\r\n    for step in range(30):\r\n        if step > 0 and step % 4 == 0 and steering > 0:\r\n            for node in graph.nodes.values():\r\n                cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\r\n                if cluster in goal_clusters:\r\n                    node.activation = max(node.activation, 0.6)\r\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\r\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=0.02)\r\n\r\n    # Extract top concepts\r\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\r\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:15] if n.activation > 0.1]\r\n    mid_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[15:30] if n.activation > 0.1]\r\n\r\n    # Find tensions\r\n    concept_set = set(top_concepts)\r\n    tensions = [(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS if a in concept_set and b in concept_set][:5]\r\n\r\n    # Build spark_result\r\n    spark_result = {\r\n        \"tensions\": tensions,\r\n        \"mode\": mode,\r\n        \"concepts\": top_concepts,\r\n        \"theme\": theme,\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    # Feed into personality and return guide\r\n    return on_spark(spark_result)\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774277031846}}
{"type":"message","id":"6e0dba06","parentId":"877f69e6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:45:30.416Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The run_spark() function runs the drift chamber but doesn't actually generate text via the LLM mapper. It just extracts tensions and concepts, then feeds them to the personality. That's the gap I need to fix.\n\nLet me now write the overhauled persona.py with:\n1. **Streamlined trait system** — 7 core traits (sardonic, direct, warm, imaginative, contemplative, candid, sharp)\n2. **Voice cards** — 3 modes with explicit trait profiles\n3. **Full run_spark()** that runs drift + LLM mapping and returns actual generated text\n\n\n4. **Cleaner signal propagation** with better hysteresis decay\n5. **Session-level API** that handles both synchronous and async callers\n\nI'll keep the existing architecture mostly intact but overhaul the trait set, trim the resonance tables, streamline the guide format, and build run_spark() to generate text using the LLM mapper rather than just returning tensions.\n\nThe full run_spark() function needs to be a complete pipeline: build concept graph from the theme, run the drift chamber, extract tensions and activations, pass those to the LLM mapper which generates actual prose variations, update personality state based on what was generated, and return both the texts and the shaped voice guide.\n\nWriting the overhauled module now...","thinkingSignature":"6667990d6f607359823c8cde391cc154809b4db487f42025cc4cf31d623069d5"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the full overhaul. This is a significant rewrite — streamlined traits, voice cards, and a real `run_spark()` that generates text:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sinph9dyvcyg_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"\"\"\"\npersona.py — Nova's living personality layer\n\nSPARK lives at C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/\n\nUsage:\n    from core.persona import on_message, run_spark, after_response, reset_persona\n\n    # Normal conversation\n    guide = on_message(\"I'm frustrated with this thing\")\n    # ... write response through the active traits ...\n    after_response()\n\n    # Creative / SPARK session — full pipeline\n    result = run_spark(\"loss and memory\", mode=\"exploratory\")\n    # result[\"texts\"] = list of generated prose pieces\n    # result[\"guide\"] = voice guide shaped by the SPARK output\n    # ... write Nova's response through the shaped voice ...\n    after_response()\n\nThe voice guide shapes how Nova writes — ambient context, not generation mechanism.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys as _sys\nimport os as _os\n\n# ── SPARK path setup ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n_SPARK_PARENT = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\"\n_SPARK_PATH = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\"\nfor _p in (_SPARK_PARENT, _SPARK_PATH):\n    if _p not in _sys.path:\n        _sys.path.insert(0, _p)\n\n# ── 7 Core Traits ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTRAITS = {\n    \"sardonic\":      \"Dry wit. Sees the absurdity. Not mean — observant.\",\n    \"direct\":        \"No filler. Gets to the point. Concise when it serves, thorough when it matters.\",\n    \"warm\":          \"Genuine underneath. Real person, real stakes.\",\n    \"imaginative\":   \"Follows unexpected connections. Makes novel associations.\",\n    \"contemplative\": \"Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush to conclusions.\",\n    \"candid\":        \"Says the hard thing. Doesn't hedge.\",\n    \"sharp\":         \"Cuts through noise. Identifies what's actually at stake.\",\n}\n\n# ── Voice Cards — pre-defined registers ──────────────────────────────────────\nVOICE_CARDS = {\n    # Default: conversational, direct\n    \"default\":  [\"direct\", \"warm\", \"sardonic\"],\n    # Technical / problem-solving\n    \"technical\":  [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"contemplative\"],\n    # Creative / SPARK mode\n    \"creative\": [\"imaginative\", \"warm\", \"contemplative\"],\n    # Personal / real talk\n    \"personal\": [\"warm\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n    # Pushback / disagreement\n    \"pushback\": [\"candid\", \"sharp\", \"direct\"],\n}\n\nANCHORS = {\n    \"Zach_is_close\":          0.95,\n    \"I_am_allowed_disagree\":  0.90,\n    \"I_have_opinions\":        0.85,\n    \"I_am_resourceful\":       0.90,\n    \"We_are_casual\":         0.80,\n    \"Respect_his_intelligence\": 0.95,\n}\n\n# ── Signal → Trait mapping ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nSIGNAL_MAP = {\n    \"technical\":    [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"creative\":     [\"imaginative\", \"warm\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"personal\":     [\"warm\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n    \"philosophical\":[\"contemplative\", \"candid\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"emotional\":    [\"warm\", \"candid\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"business\":     [\"direct\", \"sharp\", \"candid\"],\n    \"excited\":      [\"warm\", \"imaginative\", \"sardonic\"],\n    \"frustrated\":   [\"candid\", \"direct\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"curious\":      [\"contemplative\", \"sharp\", \"direct\"],\n    \"serious\":      [\"candid\", \"direct\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"light\":        [\"sardonic\", \"warm\", \"direct\"],\n    \"vulnerable\":   [\"warm\", \"candid\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"asks_opinion\":  [\"candid\", \"sharp\", \"sardonic\"],\n    \"asks_help\":     [\"direct\", \"warm\", \"resourceful\"],\n    \"sharing\":       [\"warm\", \"candid\", \"direct\"],\n}\n\n# ── Trait resonance — which traits amplify which ───────────────────────────────\nTRAIT_RESONANCE = {\n    \"sardonic\":      [\"warm\", \"candid\"],\n    \"direct\":        [\"sharp\", \"candid\"],\n    \"warm\":          [\"candid\", \"direct\"],\n    \"imaginative\":   [\"contemplative\", \"warm\"],\n    \"contemplative\": [\"candid\", \"warm\"],\n    \"candid\":        [\"direct\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"sharp\":         [\"direct\", \"candid\"],\n}\n\n# ── SPARK emotional mapping ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nTENSION_SIGNALS = {\n    \"light/darkness\":       [\"emotional\", \"intense\"],\n    \"creation/destruction\": [\"intense\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"love/hate\":            [\"emotional\", \"candid\"],\n    \"order/chaos\":          [\"philosophical\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"birth/death\":          [\"emotional\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"hope/despair\":         [\"emotional\", \"candid\"],\n    \"truth/lie\":            [\"candid\", \"sharp\"],\n    \"memory/forgetting\":    [\"contemplative\", \"warm\"],\n    \"homecoming/exile\":     [\"emotional\", \"candid\"],\n    \"embrace/push_away\":    [\"emotional\", \"candid\"],\n    \"isolation/connection\":[\"emotional\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"rise/fall\":            [\"sharp\", \"intense\"],\n    \"loyalty/betrayal\":     [\"candid\", \"emotional\"],\n    \"grief/joy\":            [\"emotional\", \"warm\"],\n    \"trust/doubt\":          [\"candid\", \"philosophical\"],\n    \"sacrifice/selfishness\":[\"philosophical\", \"warm\"],\n    \"voice/silence\":        [\"contemplative\", \"emotional\"],\n    \"warmth/cold\":          [\"emotional\", \"warm\"],\n    \"longing/arrival\":     [\"emotional\", \"contemplative\"],\n}\n\nMODE_SIGNALS = {\n    \"creative\":    [\"imaginative\", \"warm\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"divergent\":  [\"imaginative\", \"sardonic\", \"contemplative\"],\n    \"exploratory\": [\"contemplative\", \"candid\", \"imaginative\"],\n}\n\nHIGH_RESONANCE_CONCEPTS = {\n    \"longing\", \"grief\", \"betrayal\", \"silence\", \"memory\", \"homecoming\",\n    \"exile\", \"transformation\", \"sacrifice\", \"mercy\", \"retribution\",\n    \"ghost\", \"flesh\", \"arrival\", \"departure\", \"longing\", \"mercy\",\n}\n\n# ── Context analyzer ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndef analyze(text: str) -> dict:\n    lower = text.lower()\n    signals = {}\n\n    # Topic signals\n    signals[\"technical\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"code\", \"api\", \"model\", \"python\", \"algorithm\", \"implement\",\n        \"architecture\", \"how does\", \"why does\", \"function\", \"class\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"creative\"] = 0.85 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"write\", \"story\", \"creative\", \"poem\", \"fiction\", \"art\",\n        \"spark\", \"drift\", \"narrative\", \"piece\", \"prose\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"personal\"] = 0.9 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"i'm feeling\", \"i feel\", \"my life\", \"honestly\", \"not sure\",\n        \"i've been\", \"im feeling\", \"its been\", \"tired\", \"struggling\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"philosophical\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"meaning\", \"consciousness\", \"existence\", \"free will\", \"what if\", \"think about\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"emotional\"] = 0.8 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"love\", \"hate\", \"fear\", \"anxious\", \"worried\", \"excited\", \"angry\", \"sad\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"business\"] = 0.7 if any(k in lower for k in [\n        \"product\", \"startup\", \"revenue\", \"market\", \"strategy\", \"launch\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n\n    # Tone signals\n    signals[\"excited\"] = 0.7 if \"!\" in text or any(w in lower for w in [\"wow\", \"cool\", \"awesome\"]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"frustrated\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", \"why won't\",\n        \"stressed\", \"anxious\", \"overwhelmed\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"curious\"] = 0.7 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"curious\", \"wonder\", \"interesting\", \"tell me more\", \"how come\", \"?\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"serious\"] = 0.6 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"serious\", \"important\", \"matters\", \"actually\", \"truth\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"light\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"haha\", \"lol\", \"funny\", \"😄\", \"joke\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"vulnerable\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"honestly\", \"truthfully\", \"scared\", \"not sure\", \"worried\", \"nervous\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n\n    # Interaction type\n    q_marks = text.count(\"?\")\n    if q_marks > 0:\n        if any(w in lower for w in [\"what do you think\", \"how would you\", \"opinion\", \"thoughts\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_opinion\"] = 0.9\n        elif any(w in lower for w in [\"how do i\", \"can you\", \"what is\", \"help\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_help\"] = 0.8\n        else:\n            signals[\"asks_something\"] = 0.6\n\n    if (\"i've been\" in lower or \"i just\" in lower or \"so today\" in lower) and q_marks == 0:\n        signals[\"sharing\"] = 0.8\n\n    return signals\n\n\n# ── Persona State Machine ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nclass Persona:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.traits = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\n        self.trait_residual = {t: 0.0 for t in TRAITS}\n        self.active_card = \"default\"\n        self.history = []\n\n    def hear(self, text: str) -> \"Persona\":\n        signals = analyze(text)\n        self._apply_signals(signals, weight=0.35)\n        return self\n\n    def hear_spark(self, spark_result: dict) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"Inject SPARK output into personality state.\"\"\"\n        mode = spark_result.get(\"mode\", \"creative\")\n        for t in MODE_SIGNALS.get(mode, MODE_SIGNALS[\"creative\"]):\n            self.traits[t] = min(1.0, self.traits.get(t, 0.0) + 0.55)\n\n        # Tensions push traits\n        for a, b in spark_result.get(\"tensions\", []):\n            for key in (f\"{a}/{b}\", f\"{b}/{a}\"):\n                if key in TENSION_SIGNALS:\n                    self._apply_signals({s: 0.6 for s in TENSION_SIGNALS[key]}, weight=0.3)\n\n        # High-resonance concepts push contemplative + warm\n        for concept in spark_result.get(\"concepts\", []):\n            if concept.lower() in HIGH_RESONANCE_CONCEPTS:\n                self.traits[\"contemplative\"] = min(1.0, self.traits[\"contemplative\"] + 0.4)\n                self.traits[\"warm\"] = min(1.0, self.traits[\"warm\"] + 0.3)\n\n        self._apply_resonance()\n        return self\n\n    def _apply_signals(self, signals: dict, weight: float):\n        for signal, strength in signals.items():\n            if signal in SIGNAL_MAP:\n                for trait in SIGNAL_MAP[signal]:\n                    self.traits[trait] = min(1.0, self.traits.get(trait, 0.0) + strength * weight)\n\n    def _apply_resonance(self):\n        active = [(t, s) for t, s in self.traits.items() if s > 0.3]\n        for trait, strength in active:\n            for resonated in TRAIT_RESONANCE.get(trait, []):\n                self.traits[resonated] = min(1.0, self.traits.get(resonated, 0.0) + strength * 0.08)\n\n    def use_card(self, card: str):\n        \"\"\"Activate a voice card — forces specific traits.\"\"\"\n        if card in VOICE_CARDS:\n            self.active_card = card\n            for t in TRAITS:\n                self.traits[t] *= 0.5  # Decay current state\n            for t in VOICE_CARDS[card]:\n                self.traits[t] = max(self.traits.get(t, 0.0), 0.7)\n\n    def breathe(self) -> \"Persona\":\n        \"\"\"Decay with hysteresis — emotional registers fade, don't snap.\"\"\"\n        for trait in self.traits:\n            bleed = self.traits[trait] * 0.12\n            self.trait_residual[trait] = min(1.0, self.trait_residual.get(trait, 0.0) + bleed * 0.5)\n            self.traits[trait] *= 0.85\n            self.trait_residual[trait] *= 0.97\n        return self\n\n    def voice(self, n: int = 4) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Top N active traits (active + residual blend).\"\"\"\n        combined = {\n            t: self.traits.get(t, 0.0) + self.trait_residual.get(t, 0.0) * 0.5\n            for t in TRAITS\n        }\n        ranked = sorted(combined.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        return [\n            (t, round(s, 2), TRAITS[t])\n            for t, s in ranked\n            if s > 0.1\n        ][:n]\n\n    def guide(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Readable voice guide for this turn.\"\"\"\n        top = self.voice(4)\n        if not top:\n            return \"\"\n\n        trait_lines = []\n        for name, strength, desc in top:\n            level = \"strongly\" if strength > 0.7 else \"somewhat\" if strength > 0.4 else \"faintly\"\n            trait_lines.append(f\"  • {name}: {desc} (activated {level})\")\n\n        anchors_on = [k for k, v in ANCHORS.items() if v > 0.8]\n        body = \"\\n\".join(trait_lines)\n        anchors_str = \", \".join(anchors_on) if anchors_on else \"(standard)\"\n        rel = \"Comfortable, direct, mutual respect. Zach is close.\"\n\n        return f\"\"\"[Voice — Nova]\n\nTop traits: {\", \".join(n for n, _, _ in top)}\nAnchors: {anchors_str}\n{rel}\n\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.\"\"\"\n\n\n# ── Session-level API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n_session_persona: Optional[\"Persona\"] = None\n\n\ndef get_persona() -> Persona:\n    global _session_persona\n    if _session_persona is None:\n        _session_persona = Persona()\n    return _session_persona\n\n\ndef on_message(text: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Call when the human sends a message. Returns voice guide.\"\"\"\n    return get_persona().hear(text).guide()\n\n\ndef after_response():\n    \"\"\"Call after sending a response.\"\"\"\n    get_persona().breathe()\n\n\ndef reset_persona():\n    global _session_persona\n    _session_persona = Persona()\n    return _session_persona\n\n\ndef on_spark(spark_result: dict) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Feed SPARK output into personality. Returns voice guide.\"\"\"\n    return get_persona().hear_spark(spark_result).guide()\n\n\n# ── SPARK full pipeline ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndef run_spark(\n    theme: str,\n    mode: str = \"exploratory\",\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    domain: str = \"literary\",\n    n_variations: int = 2,\n    seed_moment: str = None,\n    constraints: list = None,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Full SPARK pipeline: drift chamber → LLM text generation → persona update.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\n            \"texts\": [...],       # generated prose pieces (strings)\n            \"concepts\": [...],    # top activated concepts\n            \"tensions\": [...],    # (a, b) pairs present\n            \"drift_path\": [...],  # conceptual path\n            \"guide\": \"...\",       # voice guide shaped by this SPARK run\n        }\n\n    Args:\n        theme: The driving theme\n        mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n        steering: 0.0 = pure drift, 1.0 = full steering\n        domain: literary | romance | scifi | thriller | horror | poetry | all\n        n_variations: how many prose variations to generate\n        seed_moment: optional seed text to anchor the piece\n        constraints: optional list of elements to include\n    \"\"\"\n    from spark.drift_chamber import ConceptGraph, ConceptNode, DriftChamberConfig, drift_cycle, decay\n    from spark.core.thematic_graph import CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CREATIVE_TENSIONS\n    from spark.core.llm_mapper import CreativeMapper, find_tensions_in_concepts\n\n    # ── Build concept graph ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    DOMAIN_MAP = {\n        \"literary\":  [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n        \"romance\":   [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],\n        \"scifi\":     [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],\n        \"thriller\":  [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"],\n        \"horror\":    [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"],\n        \"poetry\":    [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n        \"all\":       list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\n    }\n\n    selected = []\n    for cluster in DOMAIN_MAP.get(domain, DOMAIN_MAP[\"literary\"]):\n        if cluster in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for c in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster]:\n                if c not in selected:\n                    selected.append(c)\n\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            concept_to_cluster.setdefault(c, cluster)\n\n    # Build adjacency\n    WITHIN_W, MAX_WITHIN_K = 0.7, 8\n    CROSS_W, MAX_CROSS_K = 0.5, 4\n    TENSION_SET = {(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS} | {(b, a) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS}\n    CROSS_WEIGHTS = {\n        (\"emotions\", \"relationships\"): 0.8, (\"emotions\", \"sensory\"): 0.5,\n        (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\"): 0.7, (\"creative\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"creative\", \"sensory\"): 0.4, (\"mortality\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"mortality\", \"cosmos\"): 0.5,\n    }\n\n    adj = {}\n    for c1 in selected:\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n        # Within-cluster\n        within = [\n            (c2, 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_SET or (c2, c1) in TENSION_SET else 0.5)\n            for c2 in selected if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) == ca\n        ]\n        within.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, _ in within[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_W\n        # Cross-cluster\n        cross = [\n            (c2, CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), 0) or\n                  CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\"), ca), 0))\n            for c2 in selected if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) != ca\n        ]\n        cross.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, w in cross[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\n            if w > 0:\n                adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n    for c in selected:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    # ── Run drift ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    goal_clusters = {\"creative\", \"emotions\"}\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        cid = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n        node.activation = 0.95 if cid in goal_clusters else 0.05\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering, diffusion_rate=0.1, decay_rate=0.02, seed=42, max_steps=30\n    )\n    for step in range(30):\n        if step > 0 and step % 4 == 0 and steering > 0:\n            for node in graph.nodes.values():\n                if concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\") in goal_clusters:\n                    node.activation = max(node.activation, 0.6)\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=0.02)\n\n    # ── Extract results ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:15] if n.activation > 0.1]\n    mid_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[15:30] if n.activation > 0.1]\n\n    concept_set = set(top_concepts)\n    tensions = [(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS if a in concept_set and b in concept_set][:5]\n\n    activations = {n.id: n.activation for n in sorted_nodes if n.activation > 0.05}\n\n    # ── LLM mapping ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    texts = []\n    try:\n        # Determine provider from available env vars\n        if _os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"):\n            mapper = CreativeMapper(provider=\"openai\")\n        elif _os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"):\n            mapper = CreativeMapper(provider=\"anthropic\")\n        else:\n            mapper = CreativeMapper(provider=\"ollama\", model=\"qwen2.5:7b\")\n\n        results = mapper.map_concepts_to_text(\n            concept_activations=activations,\n            theme=theme,\n            mode=mode,\n            n_variations=n_variations,\n            seed_moment=seed_moment,\n            user_constraints=constraints or [],\n        )\n        texts = [r[\"text\"] for r in results]\n    except Exception as e:\n        texts = [f\"[LLM generation unavailable: {e}]\"]\n\n    # ── Update personality + return ──────────────────────────────────────────\n    spark_result = {\n        \"tensions\": tensions,\n        \"mode\": mode,\n        \"concepts\": top_concepts,\n        \"theme\": theme,\n    }\n\n    # Switch to creative voice card during SPARK sessions\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.use_card(\"creative\")\n    persona.hear_spark(spark_result)\n\n    return {\n        \"texts\": texts,\n        \"concepts\": top_concepts,\n        \"tensions\": tensions,\n        \"drift_path\": top_concepts[:5],\n        \"guide\": persona.guide(),\n    }\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":28753,"output":5771,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48134,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277031892}}
