{"type":"message","id":"9d2e12b2","parentId":"ea280ae5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:50:30.305Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is getting tricky. The workspace isn't a package. Let me just directly import the file by its path.","thinkingSignature":"97a799b59048a7c6b227c87eb456bd9ddc4721002826bfa86a08615cdfe33695"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oye8if1cgyzb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"\nimport sys, warnings, importlib.util\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n\n# Load persona.py directly from workspace\nspec = importlib.util.spec_from_file_location('persona', r'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py')\npersona = importlib.util.module_from_spec(spec)\nspec.loader.exec_module(persona)\n\n# Also make spark available\nsys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects')\nsys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark')\n\nresult = persona.run_spark('statelessness and memory', mode='exploratory', steering=0.3, n_variations=1)\nprint('=== TEXT ===')\nprint(result['texts'][0])\nprint()\nprint('=== CONCEPTS ===', result['concepts'][:8])\nprint('=== TENSIONS ===', result['tensions'])\nprint('=== GUIDE ===', result['guide'])\n\" 2>&1","yieldMs":95000,"timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41618,"output":299,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55527,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277423091}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6fe7925","parentId":"9d2e12b2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:51:08.491Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oye8if1cgyzb_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== TEXT ===\r\nMemory drifts, unfettered by borders or bounds.\r\n\r\nA woman sits on a worn couch, her hands grasping for the edges of nothing. Her eyes, two dark pools, stare into the distance where past and present blur. The air is heavy with the scent of old books and stale tea.\r\n\r\nHer gaze settles on a faded photograph in her lap. A child's smile, captured in time, haunts her face. She touches the corner of the frame, tracing the creased edges where love and loss have left their mark.\r\n\r\nIn this moment, borders dissolve, and the weight of statelessness lifts. The woman is free to navigate the labyrinthine corridors of memory without bounds or constraints. Her thoughts meander through forgotten streets, revisiting echoes of laughter and tears.\r\n\r\nAs she sits, lost in reverie, a faint hum emanates from her fingertips. A gentle thrumming, akin to the quiet pulse of a harp string. The sound weaves itself into the fabric of her being, an evocation of longing and belonging. In this subtle music, she finds solace.\r\n\r\nA hand reaches for the camera on the nearby table. Fingers close around it, as if grasping for something tangible in the ethereal expanse of memory. A single frame is exposed, capturing the fleeting beauty of a moment suspended between life and loss. The woman smiles, her eyes crinkling at the corners, as she searches for a place to anchor herself � not in a stateless world, but in the depths of her own heart.\r\n\r\nThe photograph is taken, and with it, the frame dissolves into silence.\r\n\r\n=== CONCEPTS === ['creativity', 'imagination', 'novelty', 'innovation', 'ecstasy', 'grief', 'wonder', 'awe']\r\n=== TENSIONS === []\r\n=== GUIDE === [Voice � Nova]\r\n\r\nTop traits: warm, imaginative, contemplative, candid\r\nAnchors: Zach_is_close, I_am_allowed_disagree, I_have_opinions, I_am_resourceful, Respect_his_intelligence\r\nComfortable, direct, mutual respect. Zach is close.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":38122,"aggregated":"=== TEXT ===\r\nMemory drifts, unfettered by borders or bounds.\r\n\r\nA woman sits on a worn couch, her hands grasping for the edges of nothing. Her eyes, two dark pools, stare into the distance where past and present blur. The air is heavy with the scent of old books and stale tea.\r\n\r\nHer gaze settles on a faded photograph in her lap. A child's smile, captured in time, haunts her face. She touches the corner of the frame, tracing the creased edges where love and loss have left their mark.\r\n\r\nIn this moment, borders dissolve, and the weight of statelessness lifts. The woman is free to navigate the labyrinthine corridors of memory without bounds or constraints. Her thoughts meander through forgotten streets, revisiting echoes of laughter and tears.\r\n\r\nAs she sits, lost in reverie, a faint hum emanates from her fingertips. A gentle thrumming, akin to the quiet pulse of a harp string. The sound weaves itself into the fabric of her being, an evocation of longing and belonging. In this subtle music, she finds solace.\r\n\r\nA hand reaches for the camera on the nearby table. Fingers close around it, as if grasping for something tangible in the ethereal expanse of memory. A single frame is exposed, capturing the fleeting beauty of a moment suspended between life and loss. The woman smiles, her eyes crinkling at the corners, as she searches for a place to anchor herself � not in a stateless world, but in the depths of her own heart.\r\n\r\nThe photograph is taken, and with it, the frame dissolves into silence.\r\n\r\n=== CONCEPTS === ['creativity', 'imagination', 'novelty', 'innovation', 'ecstasy', 'grief', 'wonder', 'awe']\r\n=== TENSIONS === []\r\n=== GUIDE === [Voice � Nova]\r\n\r\nTop traits: warm, imaginative, contemplative, candid\r\nAnchors: Zach_is_close, I_am_allowed_disagree, I_have_opinions, I_am_resourceful, Respect_his_intelligence\r\nComfortable, direct, mutual respect. Zach is close.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774277468448}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef5b1a33","parentId":"a6fe7925","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:51:36.252Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The full pipeline works end-to-end. The prose is evocative and fits the theme. The only issue is:\n\n1. The `guide` text has encoding artifacts (`�`) - this is because the `guide()` method returns a string with special characters that get corrupted somewhere. Looking at the `guide()` method, it uses `—\"` which is a Unicode em-dash. That should be fine in Python 3. The issue might be the Windows terminal or the way I'm printing. Not a big deal.\n\n2. Tensions came back empty - this is because the concept graph is small (217 concepts from 4 clusters), and the tensions are defined in `CREATIVE_TENSIONS` in the thematic_graph. \n\nThe `top_concepts` are all from the `creative` cluster (`creativity`, `imagination`, `novelty`, etc.), so none of them form the tension pairs. I need to check whether the concept graph is actually being seeded with the right cluster activations - it should be getting a broader set of concepts including emotions, mortality, and other thematic areas beyond just the creative cluster. The concepts being returned are all clustering in the creative domain, which means the tension detection is failing because it's looking for pairs like `memory/forgetting` that don't exist when everything comes from the same cluster. I need to ensure the graph gets a more diverse set of concept clusters during initialization rather than just the creative ones.\n\nLooking at how the graph is built, the goal concepts are set to 0.95 activation while everything else gets 0.05, which should theoretically let non-creative concepts survive if they have strong connections. But the drift dynamics might not be spreading activation far enough to actually pull in concepts from other clusters like emotions or mortality. During diffusion, even with a 0.1 diffusion rate, the creative concepts have such a head start that they dominate before other clusters can gain traction. The real fix is probably to initialize the graph with broader activation across multiple clusters instead of concentrating it all in the creative cluster.\n\nNow I'm realizing the core issue: `goal_clusters` is hardcoded to only `\"creative\"` and `\"emotions\"`, but when the domain is literary, we're actually loading from clusters like `creative`, `emotions`, `sensory`, and `literary`. Even though `emotions` is in the goal clusters, the actual concepts returned are all from the creative domain itself. Let me trace through what's actually being selected for the literary domain.\n\nThe concepts like creativity, imagination, novelty, and innovation are all coming back as creative cluster items, which means the diffusion isn't spreading activation to the sensory and literary clusters at all—they're staying at the base activation of 0.5 and never making it into the top results. I need to either expand which clusters contribute to goal concepts, or reconfigure how the activation spreads during the drift process.\n\nLooking at the concept universe, I realize the real issue is that the graph has 217 concepts across 9 clusters, but I'm only selecting a small subset based on the domain. Those 217 concepts exist in `concept_universe.json`, so I should be pulling from that full list instead of limiting myself to just the domain-specific clusters.\n\nActually, I think the better approach is to just seed the initial activations more broadly across clusters rather than trying to fix the selection logic. If I initialize with a wider spread, the top concepts naturally become more diverse. Though I should probably trace through why sensory and literary concepts aren't making it into the selected list in the first place—they might not be in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS under those exact keys.","thinkingSignature":"3cd51618042d493e7e2d32fcbdb5ff09e7329cf43561ed5253a321563d0156e2"},{"type":"text","text":"Full pipeline works! The prose is genuinely good. Two small issues to clean up though — tensions came back empty (all top concepts cluster in \"creative\") and the guide has encoding artifacts. Let me look:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5pbn2fafknbh_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\thematic_graph.py","limit":60}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42368,"output":828,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56806,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277468494}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec6b74ac","parentId":"ef5b1a33","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:51:36.286Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5pbn2fafknbh_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nThematic Concept Graph — built from thematic/structural knowledge.\nHigh quality creative data source, no internet required.\n\nUses human-designed concept relationships instead of statistical embeddings.\nBased on how humans actually understand creative concepts.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# THEME LABELS\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCONCEPT_CLUSTERS = {\n    \"creative\": [\n        \"creativity\", \"imagination\", \"novelty\", \"innovation\", \"invention\",\n        \"originality\", \"divergence\", \"synthesis\", \"transformation\", \"recombination\",\n        \"insight\", \"intuition\", \"eureka\", \"spark\", \"emergence\",\n        \"expression\", \"artistry\", \"craft\", \"vision\", \"voice\",\n    ],\n    \"emotions\": [\n        \"longing\", \"nostalgia\", \"melancholy\", \"joy\", \"ecstasy\", \"grief\",\n        \"wonder\", \"awe\", \"dread\", \"terror\", \"hope\", \"despair\",\n        \"love\", \"passion\", \"lust\", \"yearning\", \"loss\", \"absence\",\n        \"isolation\", \"connection\", \"belonging\", \"alienation\",\n        \"ambition\", \"greed\", \"sacrifice\", \"redemption\", \"betrayal\",\n        \"courage\", \"fear\", \"resilience\", \"surrender\", \"devotion\",\n        \"memory\", \"forgetting\", \"remembrance\", \"amnesia\", \"trauma\",\n        \"identity\", \"self\", \"other\", \"mirror\", \"shadow\", \"mask\",\n        \"guilt\", \"shame\", \"pride\", \"humiliation\", \"envy\", \"compassion\",\n    ],\n    \"narrative\": [\n        \"journey\", \"quest\", \"transformation\", \"rebirth\", \"death\", \"resurrection\",\n        \"descent\", \"ascent\", \"fall\", \"rise\", \"collapse\", \"building\",\n        \"discovery\", \"secret\", \"revelation\", \"truth\", \"lie\", \"deception\",\n        \"conflict\", \"resolution\", \"tension\", \"release\", \"suspense\",\n        \"beginning\", \"middle\", \"end\", \"cycle\", \"spiral\", \"fracture\",\n        \"homecoming\", \"exile\", \"return\", \"departure\", \"crossing\", \"threshold\",\n    ],\n    \"archetypes\": [\n        \"hero\", \"antihero\", \"villain\", \"mentor\", \"trickster\", \"shadow_self\",\n        \"guardian\", \"herald\", \"shapeshifter\", \"ally\", \"threshold_guardian\",\n        \"mother\", \"father\", \"child\", \"crone\", \"sage\", \"fool\",\n        \"outlaw\", \"lover\", \"ruler\", \"creator\", \"caretaker\", \"innocent\",\n        \"explorer\", \"rebel\", \"magician\", \"wanderer\",\n    ],\n    \"sensory\": [\n        \"light\", \"darkness\", \"shadow\", \"color\", \"sound\", \"silence\",\n        \"warmth\", \"cold\", \"texture\", \"taste\", \"smell\", \"weight\",\n        \"space\", \"distance\", \"depth\", \"surface\", \"edge\", \"boundary\",\n        \"motion\", \"stillness\", \"rhythm\", \"pulse\", \"breath\", \"heartbeat\",\n        \"flesh\", \"bone\", \"blood\", \"tears\", \"sweat\", \"skin\",\n        \"glow\", \"shimmer\", \"fade\", \"blur\", \"sharp\", \"soft\",\n    ],\n    \"mortality\": [\n        \"death\", \"life\", \"birth\", \"dying\", \"living\", \"end\",\n        \"ghost\", \"spirit\", \"soul\", \"body\", \"flesh\", \"bone\",\n        \"funeral\", \"waking\", \"sleep\", \"dream\", \"nightmare\", \"vision\",\n\n[189 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774277496273}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e8689d7","parentId":"ec6b74ac","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:51:53.527Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the clusters. The \"emotions\" cluster has \"memory\", \"forgetting\", \"longing\", \"grief\" etc. The \"sensory\" cluster has \"light\", \"darkness\", \"silence\", etc. The \"narrative\" cluster has \"homecoming\", \"exile\" etc.\n\nThe issue is that the goal_clusters is `{\"creative\", \"emotions\"}` which means concepts from those clusters start at 0.95 and others at 0.05. But even with the low initial activation, during diffusion, the \"emotions\" cluster concepts should spread to the \"creative\" cluster concepts via the cross-cluster edges.\n\nWait, I think the issue might be in the `drift_cycle` function - maybe the cross-cluster diffusion isn't working as expected, or the concepts from \"creative\" dominate because they have so many more intra-cluster edges.\n\n\nLet me trace through the `drift_cycle` implementation to see how the activation spreading actually works. The adjacency weights are built to favor within-cluster connections (0.7) over cross-cluster ones (0.5), so the creative cluster concepts likely have a structural advantage that lets them stay dominant despite the initial seeding.\n\nIf I expand the goal_clusters to include all selected clusters instead of just the top two, every concept starts with equal activation, which should give the drift dynamics a fairer chance to spread influence across cluster boundaries rather than letting the initially-high creative concepts lock in their advantage.\n\nThough I'm second-guessing this approach—the whole point of having creative and emotions as goals is to bias toward imaginative content, and weakening that might shift the drift too far from the intended direction. The real issue might be that \"statelessness and memory\" as a theme naturally pulls toward abstract concepts like creativity and imagination, which happen to live in the creative cluster. If I want more varied tensions, I'd need to either expand which clusters contribute concepts or adjust the theme to evoke a wider range of emotional territory.","thinkingSignature":"970390f27a864d40caf4b95a89b1a9f2fa9edb09910532492b12b06bf7a8688d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fzfp3thmzohl_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\thematic_graph.py","offset":61,"limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":44043,"output":468,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58121,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277496288}}
{"type":"message","id":"23773ffd","parentId":"7e8689d7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:51:53.585Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fzfp3thmzohl_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"        \"sacred\", \"profane\", \"ritual\", \"prayer\", \"curse\", \"blessing\",\n        \"sacrifice\", \"altar\", \"threshold\", \"crossing\", \"passage\",\n    ],\n    \"relationships\": [\n        \"love\", \"hate\", \"desire\", \"need\", \"want\", \"devour\",\n        \"embrace\", \"push_away\", \"intimacy\", \"distance\", \"proximity\", \"absence\",\n        \"bond\", \"break\", \"repair\", \"trust\", \"betrayal\", \"loyalty\",\n        \"marriage\", \"divorce\", \"affair\", \"secret\", \"confession\", \"lie\",\n        \"parent\", \"child\", \"sibling\", \"stranger\", \"friend\", \"enemy\",\n        \"pursuit\", \"flight\", \"capture\", \"release\", \"chase\", \"escape\",\n    ],\n    \"cosmos\": [\n        \"order\", \"chaos\", \"creation\", \"destruction\", \"renewal\", \"entropy\",\n        \"law\", \"lawlessness\", \"structure\", \"fracture\", \"collapse\", \"foundation\",\n        \"balance\", \"imbalance\", \"equilibrium\", \"tipping_point\", \"critical_mass\",\n        \"power\", \"powerlessness\", \"control\", \"surrender\", \"domination\", \"submission\",\n        \"freedom\", \"confinement\", \"escape\", \"pursuit\", \"hiding\", \"exposure\",\n    ],\n    \"literary\": [\n        \"foreshadowing\", \"flashback\", \"unreliable_narrator\", \"frame_story\", \"motif\", \"leitmotif\",\n        \"allusion\", \"allegory\", \"personification\", \"metonymy\", \"synecdoche\", \"hyperbole\",\n        \"irony\", \"dramatic_irony\", \"situational_irony\", \"verbal_irony\", \"paradox\", \"oxymoron\",\n        \"juxtaposition\", \"anaphora\", \"epistrophe\", \"anastrophe\", \"enjambment\", \"stanzabreak\",\n        \"stream_of_consciousness\", \"free_verse\", \"prose\", \"paragraph\", \"chapter\", \"section\",\n    ],\n}\n\n# -------------------