{"type":"message","id":"d4bcb5c1","parentId":"23773ffd","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:52:08.944Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The \"literary\" cluster is very formal/literary-theory focused (foreshadowing, flashback, unreliable_narrator, etc.) - not useful for creative generation. The \"sensory\" cluster has \"silence\", \"warmth\", \"cold\" - useful. The \"cosmos\" cluster has \"order\", \"chaos\", \"creation\", \"destruction\".\n\nThe tensions are things like (\"light\", \"darkness\") from sensory, (\"creation\", \"destruction\") from cosmos, (\"loyalty\", \"betrayal\") from relationships, etc.\n\nThe problem: the goal_clusters is `{\"creative\", \"emotions\"}` and the concepts returned are all from \"creative\". \n\nI'm realizing the issue might be in how the graph is initialized - the goal concepts are set to 0.95 activation while everything else gets 0.05, so the non-creative clusters like sensory and cosmos start nearly dead. Even though they should diffuse into the creative cluster through cross-cluster edges, the activation gap is so massive that the creative concepts dominate before the diffusion can spread outward. The creative cluster ends up reinforcing itself while the other clusters stay suppressed.\n\nBut wait, looking at the actual output, the generated prose about statelessness and memory actually turned out quite good despite the tensions being empty. Maybe the real issue is just that the concept spread isn't as broad as it could be, and I should try a different theme to see if the tensions would actually emerge.","thinkingSignature":"7679bfbc5cf97f615d9207c46d29b76d56442c8bfaa3393cadc4bfef99f94e27"},{"type":"text","text":"The issue: only \"creative\" cluster made it into top activations, so no tensions fired. Let me fix the goal seeding to spread across all selected clusters, not just creative+emotions:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9vyeicrhfpuz_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\