{"type":"message","id":"5fcf1e4c","parentId":"0fc6affe","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:52:52.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me test again.","thinkingSignature":"82edefaba493c73e5622cf5f75b3a9e6e539ddb9aae9917ddaf254ff135ddd71"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7uz3pytxvowz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && python -c \"\nimport sys, warnings, importlib.util\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\nspec = importlib.util.spec_from_file_location('persona', r'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py')\npersona = importlib.util.module_from_spec(spec)\nspec.loader.exec_module(persona)\nsys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects')\nsys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark')\n\nresult = persona.run_spark('statelessness and memory', mode='exploratory', steering=0.3, n_variations=1)\nprint('=== TEXT ===')\nprint(result['texts'][0])\nprint()\nprint('=== CONCEPTS ===', result['concepts'])\nprint('=== TENSIONS ===', result['tensions'])\n\" 2>&1","yieldMs":95000,"timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47140,"output":256,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61006,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277566456}}
{"type":"message","id":"54dd242f","parentId":"5fcf1e4c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:53:27.612Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7uz3pytxvowz_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== TEXT ===\r\nThe photograph lies flat on the table, its edges worn and creased. A passport, once a symbol of identity, now a relic of a forgotten home. The face in the photo, once bright with hope, has faded like the sun on a winter's day.\r\n\r\nIn the corner, a thread from a torn seam catches the light, a tiny fragment of a life left behind. The background is a blur, a hazy outline of streets and buildings that seem to shift and writhe like a living thing. It's as if the very fabric of memory has become distorted, like a funhouse mirror reflecting the past.\r\n\r\nA faint scent of smoke wafts up from the photo, carried on the stillness of the air. It's a smell of fire and ash, of flames that consumed everything in their path. The warmth of the photograph seems to seep into my skin, a gentle heat that spreads like a slow-burning ember.\r\n\r\nBut alongside this warmth, I sense a chill, a draft that whispers secrets in my ear. It's the sound of footsteps, faint but insistent, echoing through the silence like a call from beyond the grave. The light and darkness seem to be pulling apart, revealing hidden textures and contours that were once invisible.\r\n\r\nIn this moment, I'm not sure what I'm looking at � or what I'm trying to remember. All I know is that something has emerged, a spark of recognition that refuses to be extinguished.\r\n\r\n=== CONCEPTS === ['light', 'darkness', 'color', 'sound', 'silence', 'warmth', 'cold', 'texture', 'invention', 'originality', 'divergence', 'synthesis', 'transformation', 'recombination', 'insight']\r\n=== TENSIONS === [('light', 'darkness')]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":35042,"aggregated":"=== TEXT ===\r\nThe photograph lies flat on the table, its edges worn and creased. A passport, once a symbol of identity, now a relic of a forgotten home. The face in the photo, once bright with hope, has faded like the sun on a winter's day.\r\n\r\nIn the corner, a thread from a torn seam catches the light, a tiny fragment of a life left behind. The background is a blur, a hazy outline of streets and buildings that seem to shift and writhe like a living thing. It's as if the very fabric of memory has become distorted, like a funhouse mirror reflecting the past.\r\n\r\nA faint scent of smoke wafts up from the photo, carried on the stillness of the air. It's a smell of fire and ash, of flames that consumed everything in their path. The warmth of the photograph seems to seep into my skin, a gentle heat that spreads like a slow-burning ember.\r\n\r\nBut alongside this warmth, I sense a chill, a draft that whispers secrets in my ear. It's the sound of footsteps, faint but insistent, echoing through the silence like a call from beyond the grave. The light and darkness seem to be pulling apart, revealing hidden textures and contours that were once invisible.\r\n\r\nIn this moment, I'm not sure what I'm looking at � or what I'm trying to remember. All I know is that something has emerged, a spark of recognition that refuses to be extinguished.\r\n\r\n=== CONCEPTS === ['light', 'darkness', 'color', 'sound', 'silence', 'warmth', 'cold', 'texture', 'invention', 'originality', 'divergence', 'synthesis', 'transformation', 'recombination', 'insight']\r\n=== TENSIONS === [('light', 'darkness')]","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774277607600}}
{"type":"message","id":"213d3e0c","parentId":"54dd242f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:53:38.328Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now we have proper concept spread across sensory and creative clusters, and the tension `light/darkness` fired! The prose is evocative and the theme of statelessness is present. The concept spread includes sensory (light, darkness, silence, warmth, cold) and creative (invention, originality, divergence) concepts. The tension `('light', 'darkness')` fired because both are in the top concepts.\n\nThis is working well now. Let me commit these fixes.","thinkingSignature":"a86de6ab26b8a80f972c206ee47a3226a0a9458c50fe7e75eff593c98e9d547a"},{"type":"text","text":"That's the goods. Now we have sensory + creative concepts mixing, the `light/darkness` tension fired, and the prose is atmospheric. Let me commit the fixes:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fjmmmpyao0t4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && git add core/persona.py && git diff --cached --stat && git commit -m \"fix: SPARK pipeline — Ollama model detection, uniform cluster seeding, tension fixes\n\n- Ollama: detect available models at runtime instead of hardcoding qwen2.5\n- Cluster seeding: all selected clusters start at 0.75 (was: creative+emotions at 0.95, rest at 0.05)\n  → produces wider concept spread, tensions now fire\n- Removed stale step-boost loop that referenced deleted goal_clusters\n- Verified: light/darkness tension fires, concepts span sensory+creative clusters\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":47771,"output":302,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61683,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774277607614}}
