{"type":"message","id":"be75554d","parentId":"8540d5de","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:08:09.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking about hosting the SPARK API. Let me think about options:\n\n1. **Paperspace Gradient** - Zach already has this with an A5000. Could run FastAPI there.\n2. **Railway** - simple deployment, pay for usage\n3. **PythonAnywhere** - mentioned in PRODUCT.md but has limitations\n4. **Fly.io** - good for containers, reasonable pricing\n5. **Render** - similar to Railway/Fly.io\n6. **AWS/GCP/Azure** - probably overkill\n7. **VPS (DigitalOcean, Linode, Hetzner)** - cheap, full control\n\n\n8. **Localtunnel / Cloudflare Tunnel** - Zach's already using cloudflared for his Telegram webhook, so this could be a quick way to expose the API without major infrastructure changes\n\nThe simplest path forward is probably containerizing the FastAPI app and deploying it to Railway or Fly.io, though I should check what's already set up in the SPARK API directory first.","thinkingSignature":"47cce8e96f820ece823ddb968e76e182762edd6c7b1a010e04fd69a28bb765f0"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check what the API setup looks like before recommending anything:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_501f10t1yh1n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\api -Recurse -Name 2>$null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":275,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":55216,"totalTokens":59780,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774278479154}}
