{"type":"message","id":"8e58573d","parentId":"662fc605","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:08:44.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the functions exist in `demo.py`. But the API main.py uses `from spark.api.routes.creative import router as creative_router` which in turn does:\n```python\nfrom spark.demo import build_thematic_graph, run_drift\n```\n\nThe `creative.py` route is importing from `spark.demo` but `spark` isn't installed as a package — it's just in the filesystem. The API scaffolding has a broken import path issue.\n\nLet me think about hosting options. Zach already has:\n1. Paperspace Gradient (A5000 30GB) — this could host the API\n2. The API would need Ollama running there too (or use OpenAI/Anthropic keys)\n\n\n3. For deployment, Railway seems like the quickest path to get something running with FastAPI\n\nThe real blocker though is that the API's imports are broken — `creative.py` can't find `spark.demo` because the package isn't properly installed. Before I recommend a hosting platform, I should probably figure out if Zach wants to fix the import structure first or work around it.","thinkingSignature":"99a4ca158c26a7da9b7165fe3edf41803d39ac473cea2a07742118c84823415c"},{"type":"text","text":"API scaffolding exists but has a broken import chain — `creative.py` imports from `spark.demo` which won't resolve in deployment. Before hosting, let me assess the realistic options:\n\n**Where to host:**\n\n| Option | Pros | Cons |\n|--------|------|------|\n| **Railway** | Fastest deploy — `railway up`, FastAPI just works, $5-10/mo | No GPU, relies on API keys for LLM |\n| **Fly.io** | Containers, GPU instances exist, cheap | More config overhead |\n| **Paperspace** | Already have it — A5000, Ollama pre-installed | No persistent URL without domain setup |\n| **PythonAnywhere** | Already mentioned in PRODUCT.md | CPU-only, no GPU, 15s request limit |\n| **Render** | Simple, similar to Railway | No GPU, slower cold starts |\n| **Cloudflare Workers** | Free tier, fast | Workers don't support Python — would need WASM/Cloudflare AI |\n\n**Honest take:** If the API is calling OpenAI/Anthropic for the LLM mapping (not running local), **Railway** is the fastest path. Spin up, push, done — $5/mo for a hobby tier.\n\nIf you want Ollama on the A5000 at Paperspace, that works too but you'd need the API deployed there and a tunnel or domain to hit it from outside.\n\n**What's the API actually going to use for LLM?** OpenAI (paid per token), Anthropic (paid), or Ollama on Paperspace (already have the GPU)? That decides which host makes most sense.\n\nAlso — the API import chain needs fixing before anything deploys cleanly. Want me to fix that first?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48428,"output":574,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62612,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774278506263}}
