{"type":"message","id":"44ec5c10","parentId":"3b696fc9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:06.684Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants:\n1. Fix the API import chain first\n2. Make it so people bring their own LLM API keys (BYOK - bring your own key) — making the API a pure compute/hosting layer that's profitable without Nova having to pay for LLM tokens\n\nThis is actually a great business model — SPARK as a hosted drift chamber where users plug in their own OpenAI/Anthropic API keys. The profit comes from:\n- Hosting the drift/compute layer\n- Maybe a premium tier with better models, faster inference, more variations\n- The data generator and research API could also be BYOK\n\nLet me think about the architecture:\n\n\n- The FastAPI server handles just the drift chamber logic — building the concept graph, running the diffusion/steering cycles, extracting activations\n- Users provide their own LLM API key, and we call their provider directly with the activated concepts as a prompt\n- No need to manage API keys or pay for inference on our end\n\nFor the pricing model, the free tier could offer limited drift steps and concepts per month, with paid tiers unlocking higher throughput and more sophisticated steering algorithms. We'd charge for the compute layer itself, not the token costs. Since Zach already has Paperspace with an A5000 GPU, we could run smaller open-source models there instead of relying on external providers, which keeps costs predictable and gives users flexibility.\n\nLet me review the current API structure to see what needs refactoring, then sketch out the revised architecture.","thinkingSignature":"c86c745c95c369a3ca2e546ecd649d4f70a44165c2139dcb43805047e4ada320"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h2kx51ogzcjy_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\demo.py","limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":355,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":57851,"totalTokens":62495,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279553823}}
{"type":"message","id":"2fed66c6","parentId":"44ec5c10","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:06.712Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h2kx51ogzcjy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nSPARK — Interactive Creative Writing Demo\nDrift Chamber + Thematic Graph + LLM → Creative Text\n\nUsage:\n    python demo.py                          # Interactive mode\n    python demo.py --domain romance --steering 0.3 --n 2  # Headless\n    python demo.py --ollama-url http://localhost:11434  # Use Ollama\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport argparse\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add project root so 'spark' is importable\nSPARK_DIR = Path(__file__).parent  # .../spark/\nPROJECTS_DIR = SPARK_DIR.parent     # .../projects/\nsys.path.insert(0, str(SPARK_DIR))\nsys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECTS_DIR))\n\nfrom drift_chamber import (\n    ConceptGraph, ConceptNode,\n    DriftChamberConfig,\n    drift_cycle, decay,\n    activation_entropy,\n)\n\nfrom spark.core.thematic_graph import CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CREATIVE_TENSIONS, WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# THEME GRAPH BUILDER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef build_thematic_graph(domain: str = \"all\") -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build concept graph from thematic universe.\n    Returns (graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts)\n    \"\"\"\n    # Domain-specific concept selection\n    DOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\n        \"all\": {\n            \"clusters\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"romance\": {\n\n[434 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279566701}}
{"type":"message","id":"31019798","parentId":"2fed66c6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:10.218Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the full `build_thematic_graph` function and `run_drift` from demo.py to understand the current implementation.","thinkingSignature":"746f62365b28fbd429965ebb638a062c09f616fe59ba02f92bdc866b99c395a9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r6656bgzd72s_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\demo.py","offset":38,"limit":130}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49248,"output":89,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62947,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279566714}}
{"type":"message","id":"5110fd63","parentId":"31019798","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:10.244Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r6656bgzd72s_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def build_thematic_graph(domain: str = \"all\") -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build concept graph from thematic universe.\n    Returns (graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts)\n    \"\"\"\n    # Domain-specific concept selection\n    DOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\n        \"all\": {\n            \"clusters\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"romance\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"scifi\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"thriller\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"narrative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"literary\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"literary\", \"narrative\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"literary\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"horror\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"poetry\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n    }\n\n    if domain not in DOMAIN_CONFIGS:\n        domain = \"all\"\n\n    config = DOMAIN_CONFIGS[domain]\n\n    # Select concepts\n    selected_concepts = []\n    for cluster_name in config[\"clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected_concepts:\n                    selected_concepts.append(concept)\n\n    # Build concept_to_cluster\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            if c not in concept_to_cluster:\n                concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\n\n    # Build adjacency — SPARSE: limit per-node degree to prevent equalization\n    # Fully-connected within-cluster = all activations equalize instantly\n    # Fix: connect each node to max K nearest neighbors within cluster\n    MAX_WITHIN_K = 8   # Max within-cluster neighbors per node\n    MAX_CROSS_K = 4    # Max cross-cluster neighbors per node\n    CROSS_WEIGHTS = {\n        (\"emotions\", \"relationships\"): 0.8,\n        (\"emotions\", \"sensory\"): 0.5,\n        (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\"): 0.7,\n        (\"creative\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"creative\", \"sensory\"): 0.4,\n        (\"mortality\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"mortality\", \"cosmos\"): 0.5,\n    }\n\n    # Pre-compute tension pairs for within-cluster edge discovery\n    TENSION_PAIRS = {(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS} | {(b, a) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS}\n\n    adj = {}\n    for c1 in selected_concepts:\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n\n        # Find within-cluster candidates (prioritize tension pairs)\n        within_candidates = []\n        for c2 in selected_concepts:\n            if c1 == c2:\n                continue\n            cb = concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")\n            if cb != ca:\n                continue\n            # Score by whether they're a tension pair\n            score = 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_PAIRS or (c2, c1) in TENSION_PAIRS else 0.5\n            within_candidates.append((c2, score))\n\n        # Sort by score desc, take top K\n        within_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, _ in within_candidates[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n        # Cross-cluster edges\n        cross_candidates = []\n        for c2 in selected_concepts:\n            if c1 == c2:\n                continue\n            cb = concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")\n            if cb == ca:\n                continue\n            w = CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, cb), CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((cb, ca), 0.0))\n            if w > 0:\n                cross_candidates.append((c2, w))\n        cross_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, w in cross_candidates[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n    for c in selected_concepts:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    # Goal concepts\n    goal_concepts = set()\n    for cluster_name in config[\"goal_clusters\"]:\n\n[317 more lines in file. Use offset=168 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279570232}}
{"type":"message","id":"15d00213","parentId":"5110fd63","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:28.718Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture of the codebase. Here's what needs to happen:\n\n1. **Fix the API import chain** - `creative.py` imports from `spark.demo` which won't work. Need to move `build_thematic_graph` and `run_drift` into the spark core module.\n\n2. **BYOK model (bring your own key)** - The API should accept an `api_key` field and `provider` field. The user provides their own OpenAI/Anthropic key and we never touch their LLM costs.\n\n3. **Profitability** - The hosted layer (SPARK) charges for:\n   - The concept graph + drift engine compute\n   - Potentially a monthly subscription for usage tiers instead of token-based billing\n   - The value is in the methodology and results, not the LLM costs themselves\n\nI'm designing the API architecture where users specify their provider and key, we run the drift chamber purely on our side, then hand off the activated concepts and prompt to their LLM directly. This way we control the intellectual property layer while they pay their own API costs.\n\nFor the FastAPI routes, I'll consolidate everything into `main.py` rather than managing multiple files. On hosting, I'll use Railway for the API itself with the free tier for development, though Paperspace Gradient could work for heavier workloads. The drift chamber itself is fast—just concept graph operations with 150-200 nodes, so it runs in milliseconds with minimal CPU and memory overhead.\n\nFor the API response, I should return the drift results like concept activations and tensions alongside the generated text, so users get the full SPARK output. The key thing is I need to decouple `build_thematic_graph` from the demo file so it lives in core where it belongs, and same with the graph utilities.\n\nI'm planning to create a `spark/core/engine.py` module to hold these shared functions, then wire it into the API routes. For the BYOK model, I'll add an `llm_config` parameter to the request that lets users specify their own provider and key, then the API handles calling their LLM directly.","thinkingSignature":"e82da5b893604e3306dcd05ccda2fbfdf0d6be41eccac32c440993695593f89d"},{"type":"text","text":"Good — BYOK is the right model. The drift engine is pure CPU (fast, cheap to run), the LLM cost sits entirely with the user. Here's the plan:\n\n1. Move `build_thematic_graph` + `run_drift` into `spark/core/engine.py` (fixes broken imports)\n2. Rewrite the API routes with BYOK: user passes `{provider, api_key}` in the request, we run the drift, call their LLM\n3. Add usage tiers (free: 100 calls/mo → paid)\n\nLet me build it:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_owydgh64drkf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core -Name"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":50527,"output":591,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64728,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279570245}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f0e233c","parentId":"15d00213","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:29.351Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_owydgh64drkf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"__pycache__\r\n__init__.py\r\narxiv_concepts.py\r\nbuild_graph.py\r\nconcept_universe.json\r\nconcept_universe.py\r\nllm_mapper.py\r\nthematic_graph.py\r\nthematic_universe.json"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":607,"aggregated":"__pycache__\r\n__init__.py\r\narxiv_concepts.py\r\nbuild_graph.py\r\nconcept_universe.json\r\nconcept_universe.py\r\nllm_mapper.py\r\nthematic_graph.py\r\nthematic_universe.json","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279589338}}
{"type":"message","id":"8881fb12","parentId":"4f0e233c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:32.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at `build_graph.py` to see if any of the graph building functions are already there.","thinkingSignature":"bce947bb4abaee0e0c73f8dbb5680202990e1faee1cef46f953689fc2e471781"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7481kmuvg00w_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\build_graph.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":51179,"output":67,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64856,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279589352}}
{"type":"message","id":"c7cb4ab6","parentId":"8881fb12","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:32.450Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7481kmuvg00w_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Build high-quality concept graph with mpnet embeddings and run drift test.\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport numpy as np\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, \"C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber\")\nsys.path.insert(0, \"C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/core\")\n\nfrom drift_chamber import (\n    ConceptGraph, ConceptNode,\n    DriftChamberConfig,\n    drift_cycle, diffuse, steer, decay,\n    coherence_score, novelty_score, activation_entropy, interpret_drift_regime,\n)\nfrom sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\nfrom numpy.linalg import norm\n\nprint(\"Loading mpnet...\")\nmodel = SentenceTransformer('all-mpnet-base-v2')\nprint(f\"Dim: {model.get_sentence_embedding_dimension()}\")\n\n# Load universe\nwith open(Path(__file__).parent / \"concept_universe.json\") as f:\n    universe = json.load(f)\n\nall_concepts = [c[\"id\"] for c in universe[\"all_concepts\"]]\nprint(f\"Embedding {len(all_concepts)} concepts...\")\n\n# Batch embed all concepts\nembeddings = model.encode(all_concepts, show_progress_bar=True)\nconcept_to_emb = {c: embeddings[i] for i, c in enumerate(all_concepts)}\n\n# Verify semantic quality\ne_creativity = concept_to_emb[\"creativity\"]\ne_imagination = concept_to_emb[\"imagination\"]\ne_darkness = concept_to_emb[\"darkness\"]\ne_light = concept_to_emb[\"light\"]\n\nprint(f\"\\nSemantic validation:\")\nprint(f\"  creativity-imagination: {float((e_creativity/norm(e_creativity)) @ (e_imagination/norm(e_imagination))):.3f}\")\nprint(f\"  light-darkness:        {float((e_light/norm(e_light)) @ (e_darkness/norm(e_darkness))):.3f}\")\n\n# Build full graph with semantic edges\nprint(\"\\nBuilding concept graph...\")\ngraph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n\nfor concept in all_concepts:\n    graph.add_node(ConceptNode(\n        id=concept,\n        activation=0.5,\n        embedding=concept_to_emb[concept]\n    ))\n\n# Add edges weighted by semantic similarity\nEDGE_THRESHOLD = 0.35\nedge_count = 0\nfor i, c1 in enumerate(all_concepts):\n    for j, c2 in enumerate(all_concepts):\n        if i >= j:\n            continue\n        sim = float((concept_to_emb[c1]/norm(concept_to_emb[c1])) @ (concept_to_emb[c2]/norm(concept_to_emb[c2])))\n        if sim > EDGE_THRESHOLD:\n            graph.add_edge(c1, c2, sim)\n            graph.add_edge(c2, c1, sim)\n            edge_count += 1\n\nprint(f\"Graph: {len(graph.nodes)} nodes, {edge_count} edges (threshold={EDGE_THRESHOLD})\")\n\n# Initialize activations\ngoal_emb = concept_to_emb[\"creativity\"]\nfor node in graph.nodes.values():\n    sim = float((node.embedding/norm(node.embedding)) @ (goal_emb/norm(goal_emb)))\n    if sim > 0.5:\n        node.activation = 0.9\n    elif sim > 0.3:\n        node.activation = 0.5\n    elif sim > 0.15:\n        node.activation = 0.2\n    else:\n        node.activation = 0.05\n\n# Run experiment\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\nprint(\"HIGH-QUALITY CONCEPT GRAPH — 388 CONCEPTS, MPNET EMBEDDINGS\")\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\n\nfor steering in [0.0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3, 0.5, 1.0]:\n    g = graph.clone()\n    for node in g.nodes.values():\n        sim = float((node.embedding/norm(node.embedding)) @ (goal_emb/norm(goal_emb)))\n        node.activation = 0.9 if sim > 0.5 else (0.5 if sim > 0.3 else (0.2 if sim > 0.15 else 0.05))\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering,\n        diffusion_rate=0.1,\n        decay_rate=0.02,\n        seed=42,\n        max_steps=30,\n    )\n\n    for step in range(30):\n        _, g = drift_cycle(g, goal_emb, config)\n        g = decay(g, rate=0.02)\n\n    coh = coherence_score(g, goal_emb)\n    ent = activation_entropy(g)\n    regime = interpret_drift_regime(ent, coh)\n    strong = len(g.get_strong_nodes(0.3))\n    print(f\"  steering={steering:.2f}: coherence={coh:.3f}, entropy={ent:.3f}, strong={strong:3d} | {regime}\")\n\n# Domain-specific tests\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\nprint(\"DOMAIN-SPECIFIC TESTS\")\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\n\nclusters = universe[\"clusters\"]\n\nfor domain_name, domain_data in universe[\"domains\"].items():\n    domain_concepts = set()\n    for cluster_name in domain_data[\"themes\"]:\n        domain_concepts.update(clusters.get(cluster_name, []))\n    domain_concepts.update(domain_data[\"extra\"])\n    domain_concepts = [c for c in domain_concepts if c in concept_to_emb]\n    domain_concepts = list(set(domain_concepts))[:80]\n\n    if len(domain_concepts) < 20:\n        continue\n\n    dg = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n    for c in domain_concepts:\n        dg.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5, embedding=concept_to_emb[c]))\n\n    for i, c1 in enumerate(domain_concepts):\n        for j, c2 in enumerate(domain_concepts):\n            if i >= j: continue\n            sim = float((concept_to_emb[c1]/norm(concept_to_emb[c1])) @ (concept_to_emb[c2]/norm(concept_to_emb[c2])))\n            if sim > 0.3:\n                dg.add_edge(c1, c2, sim)\n                dg.add_edge(c2, c1, sim)\n\n    goal_emb_d = concept_to_emb.get(\"creativity\") or concept_to_emb[domain_concepts[0]]\n    for node in dg.nodes.values():\n        if node.embedding is not None:\n            sim = float((node.embedding/norm(node.embedding)) @ (goal_emb_d/norm(goal_emb_d)))\n            node.activation = 0.8 if sim > 0.4 else (0.4 if sim > 0.2 else 0.1)\n\n    dc = DriftChamberConfig(steering_strength=0.3, diffusion_rate=0.1, decay_rate=0.02, seed=42, max_steps=30)\n    for _ in range(30):\n        _, dg = drift_cycle(dg, goal_emb_d, dc)\n        dg = decay(dg, rate=0.02)\n\n    coh = coherence_score(dg, goal_emb_d)\n    ent = activation_entropy(dg)\n    regime = interpret_drift_regime(ent, coh)\n    print(f\"  {domain_name:20s}: {len(dg.nodes):3d} concepts, coherence={coh:.3f}, entropy={ent:.3f} | {regime}\")\n\n# SimLex validation\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\nprint(\"SIMLEX-STYLE VALIDATION\")\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\n\ntest_pairs = [\n    (\"love\", \"passion\"),\n    (\"ghost\", \"spirit\"),\n    (\"darkness\", \"light\"),\n    (\"death\", \"life\"),\n    (\"forest\", \"tree\"),\n    (\"creativity\", \"imagination\"),\n    (\"fear\", \"terror\"),\n    (\"longing\", \"nostalgia\"),\n    (\"machine\", \"circuit\"),\n    (\"ocean\", \"river\"),\n]\n\nfor w1, w2 in test_pairs:\n    if w1 in concept_to_emb and w2 in concept_to_emb:\n        n1 = concept_to_emb[w1]/norm(concept_to_emb[w1])\n        n2 = concept_to_emb[w2]/norm(concept_to_emb[w2])\n        sim = float(n1 @ n2)\n        print(f\"  {w1:15s}-{w2:15s}: {sim:.3f}\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279592436}}
{"type":"message","id":"198324e2","parentId":"c7cb4ab6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:46.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`build_graph.py` is the mpnet-based high-quality graph builder, not the thematic graph. The thematic graph builder is in `demo.py`. \n\nI need to create a new `spark/core/engine.py` that contains:\n1. The `build_thematic_graph` function (adapted from demo.py)\n2. A clean `run_drift` function\n3. All the helper logic needed by both the API and `persona.py`'s `run_spark`\n\nThe key issue is that `creative.py` (the API route) imports from `spark.demo`, which won't work because `demo.py` has its own path setup that won't work in deployment.\n\n\nNow I'm deciding whether to put the graph builder in `engine.py` or directly in `api/main.py`. Since `persona.py` also needs this functionality, I should create a shared `spark/core/engine.py` that both can import from, then update the API routes to use it. The critical thing is that `build_thematic_graph` relies on `WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT` from `thematic_graph.py`, which is already in core, so I can extract that logic cleanly.","thinkingSignature":"f116b505ffaa642b6f5a9686474006fadc60f76b7f6f7b04e24822fb2eb76145"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xkhy7vohzdaa_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\thematic_graph.py","offset":91,"limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53068,"output":303,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66981,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279592452}}
{"type":"message","id":"53403950","parentId":"198324e2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:26:46.067Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_xkhy7vohzdaa_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nCROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS = [\n    (\"emotions\", \"relationships\", 0.8),\n    (\"emotions\", \"mortality\", 0.7),\n    (\"emotions\", \"sensory\", 0.6),\n    (\"emotions\", \"cosmos\", 0.4),\n    (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\", 0.8),\n    (\"narrative\", \"mortality\", 0.6),\n    (\"narrative\", \"cosmos\", 0.5),\n    (\"narrative\", \"relationships\", 0.5),\n    (\"creative\", \"emotions\", 0.7),\n    (\"creative\", \"sensory\", 0.5),\n    (\"creative\", \"literary\", 0.5),\n    (\"mortality\", \"relationships\", 0.6),\n    (\"mortality\", \"cosmos\", 0.5),\n    (\"cosmos\", \"creative\", 0.3),\n    (\"cosmos\", \"sensory\", 0.3),\n    (\"literary\", \"creative\", 0.5),\n]\n\nWITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT = 0.85\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CREATIVE TENSIONS\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCREATIVE_TENSIONS = [\n    (\"light\", \"darkness\", 0.95),\n    (\"creation\", \"destruction\", 0.95),\n    (\"love\", \"hate\", 0.90),\n    (\"order\", \"chaos\", 0.90),\n    (\"birth\", \"death\", 0.90),\n    (\"hope\", \"despair\", 0.85),\n    (\"truth\", \"lie\", 0.85),\n    (\"memory\", \"forgetting\", 0.80),\n    (\"homecoming\", \"exile\", 0.80),\n    (\"embrace\", \"push_away\", 0.80),\n    (\"isolation\", \"connection\", 0.75),\n    (\"rise\", \"fall\", 0.75),\n    (\"identity\", \"other\", 0.75),\n    (\"ghost\", \"flesh\", 0.70),\n    (\"sacred\", \"profane\", 0.70),\n    (\"retribution\", \"mercy\", 0.70),\n    (\"transformation\", \"stasis\", 0.65),\n    (\"confession\", \"secret\", 0.65),\n    (\"pursuit\", \"escape\", 0.65),\n    (\"intimacy\", \"distance\", 0.60),\n]\n\n\n\n[109 more lines in file. Use offset=141 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279606053}}
{"type":"message","id":"020013e8","parentId":"53403950","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:27:26.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have enough context. Let me create `spark/core/engine.py` that replaces the demo.py dependency. It will contain:\n\n1. `build_thematic_graph(domain)` - returns (graph, concept_to_cluster, all_concepts)\n2. `run_drift(graph, concept_to_cluster, steering, steps, seed)` - runs the drift\n\nThen rewrite `api/main.py` and `api/routes/creative.py` to:\n1. Import from `spark.core.engine`\n2. Support BYOK (provider + api_key in request)\n3. Clean structure\n\nLet me also think about the BYOK pricing model:\n\n\n- Free tier: 100 calls/month\n- Starter $9/mo: 1,000 calls/month\n- Pro $29/mo: 10,000 calls/month\n- Enterprise: unlimited\n\nFor the BYOK implementation, the user provides their API key directly in the request, and we pass it through to the LLM mapper. This is secure since the key only goes to the LLM provider. Rate limiting and tier enforcement happen at the API gateway level.\n\nNow I'll start building out the implementation.","thinkingSignature":"4e9ec867df1aaa7aa18b3618fcba1d91dd98ff28d7ea0af2ab385a6897289930"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Let me build `spark/core/engine.py` and rewrite the API with BYOK:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bn8b4tq3829d_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"\"\"\"\nspark.core.engine — The SPARK drift engine\n\nClean import target for both the API server and persona.run_spark().\nNo path-hacking, no demo.py dependency.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Tuple, Optional\n\n# Drift chamber lives at projects/drift-chamber/\n_DRIFT_PATH = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"drift-chamber\"\nif str(_DRIFT_PATH) not in sys.path:\n    sys.path.insert(0, str(_DRIFT_PATH))\n\nfrom drift_chamber import (\n    ConceptGraph,\n    ConceptNode,\n    DriftChamberConfig,\n    drift_cycle,\n    decay,\n    activation_entropy,\n)\n\nfrom spark.core.thematic_graph import (\n    CONCEPT_CLUSTERS,\n    CREATIVE_TENSIONS,\n    CROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS,\n    WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT,\n)\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Domain configs\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\nDOMAIN_CONFIGS: Dict[str, dict] = {\n    \"all\":      {\"clusters\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),           \"goal_clusters\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys())},\n    \"romance\":  {\"clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"], \"goal_clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\"]},\n    \"scifi\":    {\"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],      \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"creative\"]},\n    \"thriller\": {\"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"], \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"narrative\"]},\n    \"literary\": {\"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"literary\", \"narrative\"], \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"literary\"]},\n    \"horror\":   {\"clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"], \"goal_clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\"]},\n    \"poetry\":   {\"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"], \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"sensory\"]},\n}\n\nTENSION_SET = {(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS} | {(b, a) for a, b, _, in CREATIVE_TENSIONS}\n\nMAX_WITHIN_K = 8\nMAX_CROSS_K = 4\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Graph builder\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef build_thematic_graph(\n    domain: str = \"all\",\n    seed: int = 42,\n) -> Tuple[ConceptGraph, Dict[str, str], List[str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build a thematic concept graph for the given domain.\n\n    Returns:\n        graph: ConceptGraph with nodes and edges\n        concept_to_cluster: mapping of concept name → cluster name\n        all_concepts: ordered list of selected concept names\n    \"\"\"\n    if domain not in DOMAIN_CONFIGS:\n        domain = \"all\"\n\n    cfg = DOMAIN_CONFIGS[domain]\n\n    # Select concepts from clusters\n    selected = []\n    for cluster_name in cfg[\"clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected:\n                    selected.append(concept)\n\n    # concept → cluster mapping\n    concept_to_cluster: Dict[str, str] = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            concept_to_cluster.setdefault(c, cluster_name)\n\n    # Cross-cluster weight lookup\n    cross_w: Dict[Tuple[str, str], float] = {}\n    for ca, cb, w in CROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS:\n        cross_w[(ca, cb)] = w\n        cross_w[(cb, ca)] = w\n\n    # Build adjacency\n    adj: Dict[Tuple[str, str], float] = {}\n    for c1 in selected:\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n\n        # Within-cluster edges\n        within = [\n            (c2, 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_SET or (c2, c1) in TENSION_SET else 0.5)\n            for c2 in selected\n            if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) == ca\n        ]\n        within.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, _ in within[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n        # Cross-cluster edges\n        cross = [\n            (c2, cross_w.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), 0))\n            for c2 in selected\n            if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) != ca\n        ]\n        cross.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, w in cross[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\n            if w > 0:\n                adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=seed)\n    for c in selected:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    return graph, concept_to_cluster, selected\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Drift runner\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef run_drift(\n    graph: ConceptGraph,\n    concept_to_cluster: Dict[str, str],\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    steps: int = 30,\n    seed: int = 42,\n) -> Tuple[ConceptGraph, List[ConceptNode]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run the drift dynamics on a pre-built graph.\n\n    Args:\n        graph: built concept graph\n        concept_to_cluster: cluster mapping\n        steering: 0.0 (pure drift) → 1.0 (pure steering)\n        steps: number of drift cycles\n        seed: random seed\n\n    Returns:\n        graph: graph with updated activations\n        history: list of node snapshots per step (last step)\n    \"\"\"\n    goal_clusters = {c for c in set(concept_to_cluster.values())}\n\n    # Seed activations — all selected clusters start at high activation uniformly\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        cid = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n        node.activation = 0.75 if cid in goal_clusters else 0.1\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering,\n        diffusion_rate=0.1,\n        decay_rate=0.02,\n        seed=seed,\n        max_steps=steps,\n    )\n\n    history = []\n    for step in range(steps):\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=0.02)\n        if step == steps - 1:\n            history = [n for n in graph.nodes.values()]\n\n    return graph, history\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# High-level: build + run in one call\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef spark_drift(\n    theme: str,\n    domain: str = \"literary\",\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    steps: int = 30,\n    seed: int = 42,\n) -> Dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    One-shot: build graph + run drift + extract results.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\n            \"graph\": ConceptGraph,\n            \"concept_to_cluster\": dict,\n            \"all_concepts\": list,\n            \"activations\": {concept: activation},\n            \"top_concepts\": list[str],\n            \"tensions\": list[(a, b)],\n            \"entropy\": float,\n            \"n_strong\": int,\n        }\n    \"\"\"\n    graph, concept_to_cluster, all_concepts = build_thematic_graph(domain, seed)\n    graph, history = run_drift(graph, concept_to_cluster, steering, steps, seed)\n\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    activations = {n.id: n.activation for n in sorted_nodes}\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:15] if n.activation > 0.1]\n\n    # Find tensions in top concepts\n    concept_set = set(top_concepts)\n    tensions = [\n        (a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS\n        if a in concept_set and b in concept_set\n    ][:5]\n\n    entropy = activation_entropy(graph)\n    n_strong = len([n for n in graph.nodes.values() if n.activation > 0.3])\n\n    return {\n        \"graph\": graph,\n        \"concept_to_cluster\": concept_to_cluster,\n        \"all_concepts\": all_concepts,\n        \"activations\": activations,\n        \"top_concepts\": top_concepts,\n        \"tensions\": tensions,\n        \"entropy\": entropy,\n        \"n_strong\": n_strong,\n    }\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\engine.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":53922,"output":2197,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69729,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279606068}}
