{"type":"message","id":"9493de1b","parentId":"d10620f6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:29:21.347Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The activations are all clustered at 0.223 — they never differentiated! This means the diffusion is too strong and the decay is bringing everything down to the same level. With 30 steps of decay at 0.02 rate and no re-boosting, everything converges to ~0.5 * (decay^30) = flat.\n\nThe issue is that with uniform initial activation (all 0.75), the diffusion spreads activation equally everywhere, and decay brings everything down uniformly without any surviving peaks.\n\nThe problem is the uniform seeding: with 133 concepts all at 0.75, after one diffusion step they're all roughly equal. Then decay keeps shrinking them uniformly.\n \nI need to switch to non-uniform seeding based on semantic similarity to the theme, add periodic re-boosting to maintain peaks during the run, and increase the diffusion rate so high-activation nodes can dominate their neighbors. Let me look at how `run_spark` in persona.py handles this differently — it uses goal clusters to determine which concepts get boosted during steps.\n\nThe real issue is that all nodes start equally in the engine, so they're all decaying at the same rate without any peaks forming. I'll fix this by adding a step-based re-boost during the drift loop that reinforces the most activated concepts, similar to what persona.py already does.\n\nWith 100 concepts all at 0.75 activation, diffusion spreads that activation equally across the fully connected neighborhoods, so everything stays balanced. Adding random noise to the initial activations and periodically re-boosting the top concepts should break this symmetry and let peaks actually emerge.\n\nNow I'm checking the math on the decay rate—with 30 steps at 0.02 decay, the activation should be multiplied by 0.98 each time, but they're all landing at 0.223 which doesn't match that calculation. Let me trace through what's actually happening in the drift cycle itself to see where the discrepancy is. The real problem is that the nodes are clustering at identical activation levels around 0.22-0.23 because the decay is too aggressive relative to the diffusion, so even with steering, nothing can break away from the pack. I need to fix this by reducing the decay rate to 0.005, seeding with much more variation (top concepts at 0.95, others at 0.05), and adding periodic re-boosts every 4 steps during the drift cycle.","thinkingSignature":"def6d59af77329c0932c9c2b27bdc8e75749ed40a88603eaac62274611deed3a"},{"type":"text","text":"The activations are all equalizing to ~0.22 — the decay rate is too high relative to diffusion, everything flattens. Let me fix the drift dynamics:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x94tev3ui6tm_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\engine.py","oldText":"def run_drift(\n    graph: ConceptGraph,\n    concept_to_cluster: Dict[str, str],\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    steps: int = 30,\n    seed: int = 42,\n) -> Tuple[ConceptGraph, List[ConceptNode]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run the drift dynamics on a pre-built graph.\n\n    Args:\n        graph: built concept graph\n        concept_to_cluster: cluster mapping\n        steering: 0.0 (pure drift) → 1.0 (pure steering)\n        steps: number of drift cycles\n        seed: random seed\n\n    Returns:\n        graph: graph with updated activations\n        history: list of node snapshots per step (last step)\n    \"\"\"\n    goal_clusters = {c for c in set(concept_to_cluster.values())}\n\n    # Seed activations — all selected clusters start at high activation uniformly\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        cid = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n        node.activation = 0.75 if cid in goal_clusters else 0.1\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering,\n        diffusion_rate=0.1,\n        decay_rate=0.02,\n        seed=seed,\n        max_steps=steps,\n    )\n\n    history = []\n    for step in range(steps):\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=0.02)\n        if step == steps - 1:\n            history = [n for n in graph.nodes.values()]\n\n    return graph, history","newText":"def run_drift(\n    graph: ConceptGraph,\n    concept_to_cluster: Dict[str, str],\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    steps: int = 30,\n    seed: int = 42,\n) -> Tuple[ConceptGraph, List[ConceptNode]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run the drift dynamics on a pre-built graph.\n\n    Args:\n        graph: built concept graph\n        concept_to_cluster: cluster mapping\n        steering: 0.0 (pure drift) → 1.0 (pure steering)\n        steps: number of drift cycles\n        seed: random seed\n\n    Returns:\n        graph: graph with updated activations\n        history: list of node snapshots per step (last step)\n    \"\"\"\n    import random\n    random.seed(seed)\n\n    goal_clusters = {c for c in set(concept_to_cluster.values())}\n\n    # Non-uniform seed with small noise — pure uniform seeding causes equalization\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        cid = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n        base = 0.85 if cid in goal_clusters else 0.15\n        noise = random.uniform(-0.05, 0.05)\n        node.activation = max(0.05, min(0.98, base + noise))\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering,\n        diffusion_rate=0.15,   # higher — active nodes pull neighbors up\n        decay_rate=0.005,      # much lower — let diffusion create differentiation\n        seed=seed,\n        max_steps=steps,\n    )\n\n    history = []\n    for step in range(steps):\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=0.005)\n\n        # Periodic re-boost: every 5 steps, reinforce goal clusters\n        # This prevents total decay collapse and maintains regime separation\n        if steering > 0 and step > 0 and step % 5 == 0:\n            for node in graph.nodes.values():\n                cid = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n                if cid in goal_clusters:\n                    node.activation = max(node.activation, 0.65)\n\n        if step == steps - 1:\n            history = [n for n in graph.nodes.values()]\n\n    return graph, history"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60487,"output":1387,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75484,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279731641}}
