{"type":"message","id":"c9ead690","parentId":"e8fa1fee","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:29:49.073Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, now they're all at exactly 0.5 with strong=133 (all of them) — this is actually the maximum entropy state where everything is equal. The diffusion_rate=0.15 might be too high. With 133 nodes all equally connected, they're all reinforcing each other equally.\n\nWait — `n_strong` is 133 which means ALL concepts have activation > 0.3. That's not differentiation either.\n\nThe issue is the `drift_cycle` function — with `diffusion_rate=0.15` and uniform-ish seeding, all nodes converge to 0.5 (equilibrium). \n\nLet me check what `drift_cycle` actually does. \n\nI think the real problem is that my step 0 seed has too much variance, so by step 1 when I re-boost and decay, everything collapses back to 0.5. With 133 nodes distributed across multiple clusters and a high diffusion rate, the system is hitting equilibrium too quickly. I need to either dial back the diffusion rate to something like 0.05 to preserve the clustering, or change the re-boost strategy to only reinforce the top concepts rather than all of them. Let me examine the drift_cycle implementation to understand how it handles the diffusion math.\n\nActually, looking at the math more carefully: with a decay rate of 0.005, a single diffusion step barely changes anything since it's just multiplying by 0.995. The real culprit is the re-boost kicking in too frequently — every 5 steps — which is keeping everything pinned at 0.65. I should try reducing the re-boost frequency to every 10 steps instead.\n\nBut stepping back, the actual problem is that my concept graph is too dense with 133 nodes where every node connects to multiple neighbors, so diffusion immediately equalizes everything. The re-boost strategy of boosting an entire cluster at once is wrong — I should only boost the top-k nodes by activation to let them differentiate. Though honestly, I'm probably overthinking this. The real issue is that in my `persona.py` version, the re-boost correctly limited itself to specific goal clusters, which actually worked.\n\nFor this 133-node dense graph, I need a completely different approach: lower the diffusion rate to prevent immediate equalization, only boost the top-k nodes instead of whole clusters, and stop re-boosting every 5 steps since that's too aggressive. The cleanest solution is to replace my hand-rolled drift with the one from `demo.py` that actually works — that code uses a completely different seeding strategy that should handle dense graphs properly.","thinkingSignature":"1a7fcc6bcb9c1fd8ff9f400e1e8745ab13dbcefc27b59381d3549d41a2033b98"},{"type":"text","text":"Still equalizing — the re-boost strategy isn't right for 133-node dense graphs. Let me check what `demo.py`'s `run_drift` actually does and use a proven approach:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oofmua6ovryz_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\demo.py","offset":180,"limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62516,"output":623,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76749,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279773450}}
{"type":"message","id":"d16f0d51","parentId":"c9ead690","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:29:49.119Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oofmua6ovryz_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def run_drift(\n    graph: ConceptGraph,\n    concept_to_cluster: dict,\n    goal_concepts: set,\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    steps: int = 30,\n    diffusion_rate: float = 0.1,\n    decay_rate: float = 0.02,\n) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run drift cycle on the thematic graph.\n    Returns (final_graph, top_concepts, activation_history)\n\n    Note: steering uses cluster-based approach since thematic graph has no embeddings.\n    Goal-cluster nodes get periodic re-activation to counteract diffusion entropy.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Identify goal clusters\n    goal_clusters = set()\n    for concept, cluster in concept_to_cluster.items():\n        if concept in goal_concepts:\n            goal_clusters.add(cluster)\n\n    # Initialize: goal-cluster HIGH, others LOW\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        if node.id in goal_concepts:\n            node.activation = 0.95\n        else:\n            cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n            if cluster in goal_clusters:\n                node.activation = 0.5\n            else:\n                node.activation = 0.05\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering,\n        diffusion_rate=diffusion_rate,\n        decay_rate=decay_rate,\n        seed=42,\n        max_steps=steps,\n    )\n\n[265 more lines in file. Use offset=220 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279789105}}
{"type":"message","id":"3729aa56","parentId":"d16f0d51","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:30:16.810Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The key insight from `demo.py`'s `run_drift`:\n1. It uses **goal_concepts** (specific concept IDs, not just clusters) to seed — goal concepts at 0.95, their cluster-mates at 0.5, everything else at 0.05. This is much more differentiated.\n2. It has a step-4 re-boost that re-activates goal clusters: `if step > 0 and step % 4 == 0 and steering > 0: ... for node in graph.nodes.values(): if concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\") in goal_clusters: node.activation = max(node.activation, 0.6)`\n\n\n3. This cluster-based seeding creates differentiation, but it's missing from `spark_drift` since `build_thematic_graph` doesn't return goal concepts.\n\nThe fix is to modify `build_thematic_graph` so it returns the goal concepts alongside the graph and cluster mapping, then use that to initialize activations correctly in `run_drift`.\n\nUpdating both functions to thread goal_concepts through...","thinkingSignature":"d949bd5da48ee22cc1264a803179df457b962a54a0b26b08cc8f6b051cf36c0f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gkpo99743pe8_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\\core\\engine.py","oldText":"# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Graph builder\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef build_thematic_graph(\n    domain: str = \"all\",\n    seed: int = 42,\n) -> Tuple[ConceptGraph, Dict[str, str], List[str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build a thematic concept graph for the given domain.\n\n    Returns:\n        graph: ConceptGraph with nodes and edges\n        concept_to_cluster: mapping of concept name → cluster name\n        all_concepts: ordered list of selected concept names\n    \"\"\"\n    if domain not in DOMAIN_CONFIGS:\n        domain = \"all\"\n\n    cfg = DOMAIN_CONFIGS[domain]\n\n    # Select concepts from clusters\n    selected = []\n    for cluster_name in cfg[\"clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected:\n                    selected.append(concept)\n\n    # concept → cluster mapping\n    concept_to_cluster: Dict[str, str] = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            concept_to_cluster.setdefault(c, cluster_name)\n\n    # Cross-cluster weight lookup\n    cross_w: Dict[Tuple[str, str], float] = {}\n    for ca, cb, w in CROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS:\n        cross_w[(ca, cb)] = w\n        cross_w[(cb, ca)] = w\n\n    # Build adjacency\n    adj: Dict[Tuple[str, str], float] = {}\n    for c1 in selected:\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n\n        # Within-cluster edges\n        within = [\n            (c2, 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_SET or (c2, c1) in TENSION_SET else 0.5)\n            for c2 in selected\n            if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) == ca\n        ]\n        within.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, _ in within[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n        # Cross-cluster edges\n        cross = [\n            (c2, cross_w.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), 0))\n            for c2 in selected\n            if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) != ca\n        ]\n        cross.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, w in cross[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\n            if w > 0:\n                adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=seed)\n    for c in selected:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    return graph, concept_to_cluster, selected","newText":"# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Graph builder\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\ndef build_thematic_graph(\n    domain: str = \"all\",\n    seed: int = 42,\n) -> Tuple[ConceptGraph, Dict[str, str], List[str], List[str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build a thematic concept graph for the given domain.\n\n    Returns:\n        graph: ConceptGraph with nodes and edges\n        concept_to_cluster: mapping of concept name → cluster name\n        all_concepts: ordered list of selected concept names\n        goal_concepts: concepts in goal (primary) clusters — the steering targets\n    \"\"\"\n    if domain not in DOMAIN_CONFIGS:\n        domain = \"all\"\n\n    cfg = DOMAIN_CONFIGS[domain]\n\n    # Select concepts from clusters\n    selected = []\n    for cluster_name in cfg[\"clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected:\n                    selected.append(concept)\n\n    # concept → cluster mapping\n    concept_to_cluster: Dict[str, str] = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            concept_to_cluster.setdefault(c, cluster_name)\n\n    # Goal concepts: all concepts in goal clusters (primary clusters for this domain)\n    goal_concepts = [\n        c for c in selected\n        if concept_to_cluster.get(c, \"\") in cfg.get(\"goal_clusters\", [])\n    ]\n\n    # Cross-cluster weight lookup\n    cross_w: Dict[Tuple[str, str], float] = {}\n    for ca, cb, w in CROSS_CLUSTER_RELATIONSHIPS:\n        cross_w[(ca, cb)] = w\n        cross_w[(cb, ca)] = w\n\n    # Build adjacency\n    adj: Dict[Tuple[str, str], float] = {}\n    for c1 in selected:\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n\n        # Within-cluster edges\n        within = [\n            (c2, 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_SET or (c2, c1) in TENSION_SET else 0.5)\n            for c2 in selected\n            if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) == ca\n        ]\n        within.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, _ in within[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n        # Cross-cluster edges\n        cross = [\n            (c2, cross_w.get((ca, concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")), 0))\n            for c2 in selected\n            if c1 != c2 and concept_to_cluster.get(c2) != ca\n        ]\n        cross.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, w in cross[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\n            if w > 0:\n                adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=seed)\n    for c in selected:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    return graph, concept_to_cluster, selected, goal_concepts"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":63455,"output":1619,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78684,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279789122}}
