{"type":"message","id":"de423bdd","parentId":"afcf9b6e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:32:36.895Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Also let me increase MAX_WITHIN_K for the literary cluster to allow more cross-cluster connections to compensate... Actually wait, I already excluded literary from within-cluster edges. Let me also make sure literary concepts have enough cross-cluster edges (increase MAX_CROSS_K for literary nodes). But that might be overcomplicating things. Let me just test first.","thinkingSignature":"1c18dc4316c11bd72f64eb923bffd1a0a24c4c85a95610c3186d10e6571953e5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y0uv9736o8cv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark && python -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '.')\nsys.path.insert(0, '..')\nfrom spark.core.engine import spark_drift\nfor domain in ['all', 'literary', 'scifi', 'romance']:\n    r = spark_drift('statelessness and memory', domain=domain, steering=0.3, steps=30)\n    top_keys = [c for c,a in sorted(r['activations'].items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])[:8]]\n    print(domain, ': top=', top_keys, ' strong=', r['n_strong'], ' tensions=', r['tensions'])\n\" 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":72053,"output":261,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85924,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279950866}}
{"type":"message","id":"2994302b","parentId":"de423bdd","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:32:38.471Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_y0uv9736o8cv_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"all : top= ['memory', 'forgetting', 'craft', 'joy', 'paradox', 'chapter', 'chaos', 'lover']  strong= 9  tensions= [('memory', 'forgetting')]\r\nliterary : top= ['artistry', 'originality', 'motif', 'allegory', 'hyperbole', 'juxtaposition', 'stanzabreak', 'section']  strong= 8  tensions= []\r\nscifi : top= ['balance', 'control', 'order', 'chaos', 'creation', 'destruction', 'renewal', 'entropy']  strong= 27  tensions= [('creation', 'destruction'), ('order', 'chaos')]\r\nromance : top= ['want', 'ecstasy', 'grief', 'wonder', 'hate', 'desire', 'need', 'awe']  strong= 77  tensions= [('embrace', 'push_away')]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1542,"aggregated":"all : top= ['memory', 'forgetting', 'craft', 'joy', 'paradox', 'chapter', 'chaos', 'lover']  strong= 9  tensions= [('memory', 'forgetting')]\r\nliterary : top= ['artistry', 'originality', 'motif', 'allegory', 'hyperbole', 'juxtaposition', 'stanzabreak', 'section']  strong= 8  tensions= []\r\nscifi : top= ['balance', 'control', 'order', 'chaos', 'creation', 'destruction', 'renewal', 'entropy']  strong= 27  tensions= [('creation', 'destruction'), ('order', 'chaos')]\r\nromance : top= ['want', 'ecstasy', 'grief', 'wonder', 'hate', 'desire', 'need', 'awe']  strong= 77  tensions= [('embrace', 'push_away')]","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774279958452}}
{"type":"message","id":"a3bbea17","parentId":"2994302b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:32:47.714Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now `literary` is working — concepts are differentiated. The tensions are still not firing for literary though (no tensions in the literary cluster). That's OK.\n\n`all`, `scifi`, and `romance` all show tensions. `scifi` has 27 strong concepts though — that's a lot. Let me check if that's OK... cosmos cluster is 30 concepts, all of them at high activation. This is the same issue as literary before — the cosmos cluster is large. But scifi still shows tensions (creation/destruction, order/chaos), so it's still generating useful output.\n\nFor the API, this is fine. Let me now test the full end-to-end with text generation to make sure everything works:","thinkingSignature":"1a2e973e93739eb1bca5b1a5d606948789f05678c587f133a86dcb40ca8f9f01"},{"type":"text","text":"Literary works now. Let me test the full pipeline including LLM generation via Ollama:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_whd33esmws4d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark && python -c \"\nimport sys, warnings\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\nsys.path.insert(0, '.')\nsys.path.insert(0, '..')\nfrom spark.core.engine import spark_drift\nfrom spark.core.llm_mapper import CreativeMapper\n\nr = spark_drift('statelessness and memory', domain='all', steering=0.3, steps=30)\nmapper = CreativeMapper(provider='ollama', model='llama3.2:3b')\nresults = mapper.map_concepts_to_text(r['activations'], 'statelessness and memory', mode='exploratory', n_variations=1)\nprint(results[0]['text'])\nprint()\nprint('Concepts:', r['top_concepts'][:8])\nprint('Tensions:', r['tensions'])\n\" 2>&1","yieldMs":95000,"timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":72537,"output":399,"cacheRead":13610,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86546,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774279958473}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b4c17b5","parentId":"a3bbea17","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:33:32.132Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_whd33esmws4d_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In the stillness of her room, she clutched a worn photograph � a snapshot of her mother's passport. A creased paper fluttered to the floor as her fingers loosened their grip. The date stamped on its edge was from an era long past.\r\n\r\nThe stateless woman in the photo had once carried this very document with pride. She had navigated borders and bureaucracies, deftly dodging the villainous hand of expatriation. Now, it lay crumpled, a relic of a life left behind.\r\n\r\nAs she picked up the paper, her eyes fell upon the words ' expired' scrawled in red ink � like a promise broken, or a promise made. The creases on the photograph deepened as if time itself was unraveling its threads.\r\n\r\nHer mother's funeral had been a distant echo, a mournful hum that refused to fade. In the midst of chaos, she'd found solace in the quiet certainties of her homeland � only to lose it all. The loss still lingered like an open wound, refusing to heal.\r\n\r\nShe folded the photograph into a small square and tucked it between the pages of a dog-eared book. As she closed the cover, her gaze fell upon a phrase etched on the spine: 'a life without borders is a life without memory.' A secret long buried began to surface � one that would forever alter her perception of the world.\r\n\r\nIn this hushed room, where shadows danced upon the walls, she let silence be her confidante.\r\n\r\nConcepts: ['beginning', 'spiral', 'departure', 'mother', 'villain', 'funeral', 'life', 'despair']\r\nTensions: []"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":44382,"aggregated":"In the stillness of her room, she clutched a worn photograph � a snapshot of her mother's passport. A creased paper fluttered to the floor as her fingers loosened their grip. The date stamped on i